%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20know%20if%20your%20rebound%20relationship%20will%20last%2C%20according%20to%20a%20therapist%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Doing%20It%20Right%20Series%3A%20Frustrated%20woman%20looking%20off%20to%20the%20side%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580cf2250edbc52a8658215%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeople%20often%20use%20rebound%20relationships%20to%20fill%20an%20emotional%20void.%20But%20under%20the%20right%20circumstances%2C%20a%20rebound%20can%20become%20a%20strong%20connection%2C%20a%20therapist%20said.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20all%20rebound%20relationships%20are%20doomed%20to%20fail%2C%20a%20therapist%20said.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20normal%20to%20compare%20a%20current%20lover%20to%20an%20ex%2C%20but%20it%20shouldn't%20get%20in%20the%20way%20of%20a%20new%20connection.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESexual%20attraction%20is%20complex.%20Don't%20assume%20your%20fate%20is%20set%20with%20a%20new%20partner%20if%20sex%20is%20lackluster.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22doing%20it%20right%20banner%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d81117ff4fc2402cd7a53d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22151%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESamantha%20Lee%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDear%20Julia%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EI've%20been%20with%20my%20boyfriend%20for%20almost%20two%20years%2C%20and%20I%20love%20him%20so%20much.%20But%20when%20we%20first%20started%20dating%2C%20I%20was%20still%20getting%20over%20my%20ex.%20I%20didn't%20realize%20it%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20I%20now%20believe%20that%20I%20used%20my%20current%20relationship%20as%20a%20rebound.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EEarly%20on%2C%20I%20started%20comparing%20my%20boyfriend%20to%20my%20ex.%20I%20made%20these%20comparisons%20silently%20to%20myself%2C%20and%20most%20of%20the%20time%20it%20was%20to%20highlight%20how%20my%20current%20boyfriend%20is%20better%20for%20me%20than%20my%20ex.%20But%20sometimes%2C%20I%20would%20think%20about%20how%20I%20felt%20more%20sexually%20attracted%20to%20my%20ex%20than%20my%20current%20partner.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon't%20get%20me%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20when%20I%20first%20met%20my%20now-boyfriend%2C%20I%20thought%20he%20was%20really%20handsome%2C%20and%20I%20still%20do.%20Our%20sex%20life%20isn't%20horrible%20by%20any%20means.%20But%20I%20never%20feel%20fully%20satisfied%20with%20it%2C%20and%20our%20sexual%20chemistry%20isn't%20as%20strong%20as%20I'd%20hoped.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20I've%20stopped%20comparing%20my%20ex%20and%20my%20current%20partner.%20But%20I%20have%20a%20nagging%20feeling%20that%20I%20made%20a%20mistake.%20Is%20my%20relationship%20less%20likely%20to%20last%20because%20it%20was%20a%20rebound%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E-Lagos%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20Lagos%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20feel%20completely%20settled%20and%20secure%20in%20a%20relationship%20when%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20ifs%26quot%3B%20keep%20popping%20into%20your%20head%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20when%20those%20questions%20have%20to%20do%20with%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-racing-mind-during-sex-therapist-advice-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esex%20life%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20what%20you've%20told%20me%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20you%20and%20your%20boyfriend%20have%20a%20loving%20connection%20that%20you've%20worked%20hard%20to%20foster.%20Even%20when%20you%20were%20going%20through%20complicated%20emotions%20about%20the%20end%20of%20another%20relationship%2C%20you%20found%20and%20pursued%20a%20connection%20with%20someone%20else.%20That%20doesn't%20make%20you%20deceptive%3B%20it%20makes%20you%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20normal%20to%20think%20about%20an%20ex-partner%20while%20making%20memories%20with%20new%20lovers%2C%20silently%20comparing%20the%20different%20ways%20they%20think%20or%20act%2C%20therapist%20Amelia%20Kelley%20told%20me.%20This%20only%20becomes%20detrimental%20to%20future%20connections%20if%20you%20let%20it%20hold%20you%20back%20from%20getting%20close%20to%20your%20new%20partner%2C%20or%20move%20so%20fast%20that%20you%20avoid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhard-conversations-about-dating-to-normalize-how-to-have-them-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifficult%20conversations%20that%20build%20trust%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Kelley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20you're%20willing%20to%20take%20your%20time%20and%20see%20if%20it's%20a%20good%20fit%2C%20a%20rebound%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20turn%20into%20something%20more%20and%20last%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EReconsider%20how%20you%20view%20sexual%20attraction%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20connection%2C%20whether%20a%20rebound%20or%20not%2C%20will%20likely%20have%20elements%20that%20remind%20you%20of%20a%20past%20relationship.%20There's%20also%20a%20fair%20chance%20that%20being%20with%20someone%20new%20will%20bring%20fresh%20perspectives%20and%20experiences%20to%20your%20life%2C%20including%20what%20you%20talk%20about%2C%20the%20dates%20you%20go%20on%20together%2C%20and%20even%20how%20you%20have%20sex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnless%20you're%20trying%20to%20avoid%20repeating%20dating%20mistakes%20that%20you%20made%20in%20the%20past%2C%20like%20constantly%20choosing%20emotionally%20unavailable%20partners%2C%20fixating%20on%20every%20similarity%20and%20difference%20you%20notice%20is%20largely%20unhelpful%2C%20according%20to%20Kelley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20suggested%20that%20you%20try%20to%20view%20how%20your%20relationship%20started%2C%20and%20how%20you%20feel%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fnever-sexually-attracted-to-longterm-partner-what-do-i-do-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esexual%20attraction%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20your%20partner%2C%20as%20two%20unrelated%20factors.%20This%20way%2C%20you%20can%20assess%20your%20relationship%20as%20it%20currently%20is%2C%20instead%20of%20getting%20caught%20up%20in%20hypotheticals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20realizing%20a%20relationship%20is%20not%20the%20right%20one%20for%20you.%20But%20there's%20also%20a%20natural%20progression%20of%20intimacy%20in%20relationships%20that%20you%20should%20be%20aware%20of%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelley%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20time%20passes%20and%20you%20become%20closer%20to%20a%20partner%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Freasons-for-crushes-science-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erush%20of%20hormones%20that%20made%20you%20feel%20extra%20giddy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20beginning%20start%20to%20wear%20off%2C%20Kelley%20said.%20This%20physiological%20change%2C%20and%20getting%20into%20a%20comfortable%20pattern%20with%20your%20partner%2C%20can%20impact%20how%20spontaneous%2C%20exciting%2C%20and%20satisfying%20sex%20feels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelley%20also%20said%20that%20sexual%20attraction%20can%20feel%20more%20intense%20if%20it's%20towards%20someone%20who%20is%20unavailable%20in%20other%20ways.%20If%2C%20for%20example%2C%20your%20ex%20had%20trouble%20listening%20to%20your%20emotional%20needs%20or%20had%20a%20habit%20of%20prioritizing%20their%20career%20over%20quality%20time%20with%20you%2C%20sex%20could%20have%20felt%20like%20a%20lifeline%20that%20connected%20you.%20If%20you're%20getting%20more%20of%20your%20needs%20met%20outside%20of%20the%20bedroom%20than%20in%20previous%20relationships%2C%20sexual%20attraction%20might%20not%20hold%20as%20much%20weight%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20overall%20health%20of%20your%20connection%2C%20Kelley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20if%20the%20foundation%20of%20your%20connection%20is%20mutual%20love%20and%20care%2C%20you%20can%20always%20work%20on%20making%20your%20sex%20life%20more%20satisfying%20%E2%80%94%20like%20asking%20your%20partner%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsex-script-helps-couples-transform-sex-life-therapist-advice-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexperiment%20with%20different%20types%20of%20touch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsexual-verbal-domination-how-to-do-it-according-to-dominatrix-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erole%20playing%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20out%20of%20a%20routine%2C%20or%20flirting%20more%20throughout%20the%20day%20to%20feel%20that%20sense%20of%20sexy%20urgency%20when%20you%20get%20home%20from%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20sounding%20clich%C3%A9%2C%20comparison%20really%20can%20be%20the%20thief%20of%20joy.%20But%20leaning%20into%20gratitude%2C%20by%20focusing%20on%20the%20things%20you%20love%20about%20your%20partner%2C%20could%20help%20you%20unlock%20the%20next%20level%20of%20your%20relationship.%20And%20who%20knows%3F%20It%20could%20end%20up%20blowing%20your%20mind%20(and%20your%20back%20out)%20more%20than%20your%20ex%20ever%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20a%20question%20for%20Julia%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcategory%2Fdoing-it-right%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EFill%20out%20this%20anonymous%20form.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20All%20questions%20will%20be%20published%20anonymously.%20You%20can%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.c