gh%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnapoleon-egypt-invasion-scientific-breakthroughs-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEgyptian%20heat%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201798.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20took%20power%20in%20France%2C%20Napoleon%20elevated%20doctors%20and%20scientists%20to%20positions%20of%20power%20to%20solve%20problems%20like%20this.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20men%20then%20formed%20organizations%20and%20%26quot%3Bsupported%20research%20related%20to%20food%20preparation%20and%20preservation%20that%20might%20benefit%20France's%20armies%20and%20navies%2C%26quot%3B%20historian%20Jennifer%20J.%20Davis%20wrote%20in%20%26quot%3BDefining%20Culinary%20Authority.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201809%2C%20one%20such%20organization%2C%20the%20Soci%C3%A9t%C3%A9%20d'encouragement%20pour%20l'industrie%20nationale%2C%20held%20a%20contest%20searching%20for%20food%20preservation%20methods.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicolas%20Appert%20%E2%80%94%20who%20had%20been%20sealing%20food%20in%20corked%20jars%20for%20several%20years%20and%20had%20already%20been%20experimenting%20with%20heating%20and%20bottling%20food%20for%20over%20a%20decade%20%E2%80%94%20took%20the%20prize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Appert%20method%20of%20food%20preservation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAppert%20had%20been%20in%20the%20food%20industry%20practically%20since%20childhood.%20His%20father%20was%20an%20innkeeper%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrewery-ceo-says-paid-over-500000-to-customers-over-misleading-ads-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrewery%20owner%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20he'd%20worked%20in%20distilleries%20and%20wine%20cellars%20before%20opening%20his%20own%20confectionery%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20heating%20process%20needed%20to%20make%20candy%20as%20well%20as%20the%20bottling%20process%20for%20wine%20and%20beer%20may%20have%20influenced%20his%20method%20for%20preserving%20food.%20He%20described%20himself%20as%20reared%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20art%20of%20preparing%20and%20preserving%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20lived%2C%20as%20it%20were%2C%20in%20pantries%2C%20in%20breweries%2C%20in%20store-rooms%2C%20and%20in%20the%20cellars%20of%20Champagne.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201795%2C%20he%20started%20trying%20to%20preserve%20different%20foods.%20He%20used%20empty%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fgifts%2Fbest-champagne%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChampagne%20bottles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20specially%20made%20glass%20containers.%20After%20sealing%20them%2C%20he'd%20boil%20the%20entire%20bottle%20and%20its%20contents%20in%20a%20water%20bath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20engraving%20of%20Nicolas%20Appert%20from%20the%20shoulders%20up%20wearing%20a%20high-collared%20coat%20with%20buttons%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655e4d424ca513d8242dcc9a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222799%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENicolas%20Appert%20developed%20a%20large-scale%20method%20for%20preserving%20food%20that%20was%20a%20precursor%20to%20canning.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAppert%20wasn't%20precisely%20sure%20why%20his%20method%20worked%2C%20but%20he%20believed%20limiting%20its%20contact%20with%20air%20and%20the%20water's%20heat%20were%20%26quot%3Bboth%20indispensable.%26quot%3B%20He%20was%20correct%20on%20both%20counts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20bottling%20vegetables%20and%20fruit%20like%20asparagus%2C%20cauliflower%2C%20peaches%2C%20and%20cherries%2C%20Appert%20also%20partially%20cooked%20some%20dishes%20before%20bottling%20and%20heating%20them.%20He%20made%20seasoned%20eel%2C%20mutton%20tongue%2C%20meat%20broth%2C%20and%20egg%20in%20bechamel%20sauce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20sure%20his%20food%20retained%20the%20proper%20color%2C%20aroma%2C%20and%20taste%2C%20he%20tested%20different%20times%20and%20temperatures%20for%20heating%20different%20dishes.%20Many%20probably%20wouldn't%20pass%20food-safety%20inspections%2C%20like%20the%20beef%20jelly%20that%20only%20needed%20heating%20for%2015%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20jar%20of%20preserves%20could%20cost%20a%20day's%20wage.%20For%20those%20who%20could%20afford%20it%2C%20they%20could%20open%20the%20can%20(which%20was%20actually%20quite%20a%20chore%20until%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-can-opener%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20opener%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20invented%20decades%20later)%20and%20enjoy%20almost-fresh%20green%20vegetables%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20Appert's%20method%20didn't%20catch%20on%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201810%2C%20the%20French%20Ministry%20of%20the%20Interior%20paid%20Appert%2012%2C000%20francs%20to%20print%20a%20description%20of%20his%20preserving%20process%20%26quot%3Bto%20spread%20the%20knowledge.%26quot%3B%20His%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Art%20of%20Preserving%20Animal%20and%20Vegetable%20Substances%20For%20Several%20Years%2C%26quot%3B%20sold%20thousands%20of%20copies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAppert%20has%20found%20a%20way%20to%20fix%20the%20seasons%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20one%20paper.%20Elite%20cookbook%20authors%20praised%20his%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFolklorist%20Danille%20Elise%20Christensen%20noted%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bsugarless%20water-bath%20procedures%26quot%3B%20appeared%20in%20cookbooks%20written%20by%20women%20as%20early%20as%20the%201680s.%20Stories%20that%20focus%20on%20Appert%20while%20ignoring%20Mary%20Mott%2C%20Sarah%20Martin%2C%20and%20others%20%26quot%3Bvalorize%20'scientific'%20over%20and%20against%20'domestic'%20knowledge%2C%26quot%3B%20Christensen%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAppert%20had%20been%20able%20to%20scale%20his%20technique%2C%20at%20one%20point%20employing%20fifty%20cooks%20to%20help%20make%20his%20preserved%20dishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20processes%2C%20including%20drying%20and%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fwhat-are-preservatives%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esalt%20and%20sugar%20to%20preserve%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20endured%20after%20Appert%20published%20his%20book.%20His%20method%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20used%20widely%20on%20a%20scientific%20or%20industrial%20level%26quot%3B%20outside%20of%20his%20own%20factory%2C%20according%20to%20Davis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20French%20navy%20had%20trialed%20Appert's%20preserves%20before%20he%20wrote%20his%20book%2C%20his%20fragile%20glass%20bottles%20weren't%20practical%20for%20sea%20voyages.%20Within%20a%20few%20years%2C%20another%20French%20citizen%2C%20Philippe%20de%20Girard%2C%20went%20to%20London%20and%20patented%20his%20idea%20for%20a%20tin%20can%20through%20an%20intermediary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFrom%20glass%20bottles%20to%20tin%20cans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBryan%20Donkin%20purchased%20the%20patent%20for%20%C2%A31%2C000%2C%20and%20it%20was%20he%20and%20his%20partners%20who%20made%20the%20consumm%C3%A9%20Banks%20so%20enjoyed.%20The%20cans%20could%20weigh%20as%20much%20as%2020%20pounds%2C%20but%20they%20were%20hardier%20than%20Appert's%20bottles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20industry%20started%20spreading%20almost%20immediately.%20By%20the%201820s%2C%20the%20US%20had%20a%20few%20canneries%2C%20and%20the%20country's%20first%20patent%20for%20tin%20cans%20was%20granted%20in%201825.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222006%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20engraving%20from%20the%201800s%20of%20several%20people%20filling%20and%20soldering%20cans%20of%20food%20in%20a%20factory%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655e4c8022cf74a5739bb274%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20engraving%20from%20the%201870s%20shows%20a%20busy%20French%20cannery.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20all%20decades%20before%20Louis%20Pasteur%20developed%20his%20pasteurization%20method%20and%20realized%20bacteria%20caused%20contamination.%20His%20technique%20significantly%20reduced%20the%20number%20of%20bacteria%20without%20fully%20sterilizing%20the%20food%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20killing%20off%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fbotulism%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBotulism%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20called%20%26quot%3Ba%20disease%20of%20civilization.%26quot%3B%20Sausages%20and%20smoked%20ham%20have%20both%20caused%20deadly%20outbreaks.%20Improperly%20canned%20food%20can%20also%20harbor%20the%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20of%20the%20many%20reasons%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-shoppers-beef-chicken-save-money-food-budget-options-recession-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommercially%20sold%20canned%20goods%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20waxed%20and%20waned%20in%20popularity%20in%20the%20centuries%20since%20Appert's%20first%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20early%20success%2C%20Appert%20struggled%20with%20debt.%20When%20late%20in%20life%20he%20was%20threatened%20with%20eviction%2C%20he%20wrote%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20the%20Interior%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20gave%20my%20life%20to%20science%20and%20to%20mankind.%20You're%20taking%20away%20the%20premises%20I%20thought%20ought%20to%20be%20mine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20he%20was%20evicted%20from%20his%20lab%20in%201824%2C%20the%20Restoration%20government%20eventually%20paid%20him%204%2C000%20francs%20annually%20for%20ten%20years%20%26quot%3Bin%20recognition%20of%20his%20service%20to%20the%20nation%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Davis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffood-preservation-nicolas-appert-canning-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704106021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657a538a50edbc52a8640c19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffood-preservation-nicolas-appert-canning-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Napoleon%20needed%20to%20feed%20his%20armies.%20Nicolas%20Appert%20had%20a%20method%20of%20preserving%20eel%2C%20blackberries%2C%20and%20more.%20Here's%20how%20he%20helped%20commercialize%20canning.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffood-preservation-nicolas-appert-canning-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI%20is%20saving%20sales%20professionals%20more%20than%20two%20hours%20of%20work%20each%20day%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221732%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20drawing%20of%20a%20robot%20and%20a%20human%20employee%20doing%20work%20together.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658ef827ec62ab5daf7f946e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221299%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESales%20professionals%20are%20saving%20hours%20of%20time%20on%20manual%20tasks%20thanks%20to%20AI.%3Cp%3ETarikVision%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-sam-altman-ai-year-review-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArtificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20saving%20US%20sales%20professionals%20hours%20of%20work%20each%20day%2C%20a%20survey%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESales%20pros%20are%20using%20AI%20to%20automate%20manual%20tasks%20like%20scheduling%20meetings%20and%20note%20taking.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENearly%20a%20third%20of%20sales%20workers%20are%20using%20generative%20AI%20tools%20like%20ChatGPT%2C%20according%20to%20Hubspot.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2