%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20the%20Videla%20family%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20the%20body.%20Without%20filing%20a%20request%20for%20%3Cem%3Ehabeas%20corpus%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20you%20have%20the%20body.%20A%20few%20forms%20to%20fill%2C%20and%20it%20is%20yours%2C%20you%20can%20take%20away%20your%20relative%E2%80%99s%20mortal%20shell.%20You%20have%20a%20body.%20You%20will%20notice%20that%20it%20is%20delivered%20to%20you%20without%20any%20burns%20or%20bruises.%20We%20could%20at%20least%20have%20given%20it%20a%20richly%20deserved%20beating.%20We%2C%20however%2C%20prefer%20not%20to%20do%20the%20things%20that%20the%20body%20that%20you%20are%20going%20to%20bury%20did.%20We%20did%20not%20throw%20it%20out%20of%20a%20plane%2C%20we%20did%20not%20encourage%20it%20to%20%E2%80%9Csqueal%E2%80%9D%20using%20electric%20shocks.%20To%20squeal%2C%20for%20example%2C%20about%20where%20our%20bodies%2C%20those%20of%20our%20comrades%2C%20are.%20We%20did%20not%20rape%20it.%20We%20did%20not%20put%20its%20child%20on%20its%20chest%20while%20we%20cranked%20the%20generator.%20We%20did%20not%20shoot%20it%20in%20order%20to%20pretend%20that%20it%20died%20in%20a%20stand-off.%20We%20did%20not%20encase%20it%20in%20concrete.%20We%20did%20not%20bury%20it%20in%20an%20unmarked%20grave%20somewhere.%20We%20did%20not%20steal%20its%20grandchildren.%20Here%2C%20the%20body%20is%20yours.%20(cited%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F14623528.2018.1459230%5C%22%3ES%C3%A9vane%C2%A0Garibian%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20body%20belonged%20to%20General%20Jorge%20Rafael%20Videla%2C%20notorious%C2%A0%20Commander%20in%20Chief%20of%20the%20Argentinian%20army%20and%20%3Cem%3Ede%20facto%20%3C%2Fem%3Edictator%20between%201976%20and%201981%2C%20during%20whose%20reign%20of%20terror%20upwards%20of%2020%2C000%20persons%2C%20by%20one%20estimate%2C%20mostly%20politically%20active%20people%2C%20were%20%E2%80%98disappeared%E2%80%99.%20At%20least%2010%2C000%20of%20these%20%5Bpeople%5D%20have%20never%20been%20found%2C%20even%20as%20skeletal%20remains%2C%20and%20these%20are%20the%20subject%20of%20the%20famous%20Mothers%20of%20the%20Plaza%20campaign%20since%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKostinger%E2%80%99s%20letter%20shows%20barely%20controlled%20anger.%20Referencing%20all%20the%20horrific%20modes%20of%20torture%20performed%20on%20thousands%20of%20Argentinian%20citizens%2C%20Kostinger%20tells%20the%20Videla%20family%20that%20the%20dictator%E2%80%99s%20body%20was%20never%20defiled%2C%20never%20desecrated%3A%20the%20body%20is%20intact%2C%20possesses%20its%20own%20integrity%20still%2C%20unlike%20the%20many%20victims%20of%20Jorge%20Rafael%20Videla.%20It%20is%20ready%20for%20memorialisation%20%E2%80%93%20an%20honour%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20available%20to%20his%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20much%20has%20been%20said%20and%20written%20about%20the%20mourning%20and%20memorialisation%20for%20the%20victims%2C%20the%20question%20arises%2C%20how%20does%20one%20memorialise%20perpetrators%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20perpetrator%20here%20is%20not%20a%20serial%20killer%20or%20everyday%20offenders%20of%20civil%20or%20criminal%20law%2C%20but%2C%20in%20the%20words%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sup.org%2Fbooks%2Ftitle%2F%3Fid%3D34348%5C%22%3EAntonius%20C.G.M.%20Robben%20and%20Alexander%20Laban%20Hinton%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cactive%20participants%20in%20state%20institutions%20and%20repressive%20organisations%20or%20informal%20associations%20and%20networks%20who%20carry%20out%20genocide%2C%20mass%20killings%2C%20or%20violent%20acts%20for%20the%20presumed%20greater%20good%20of%20the%20state%2C%20a%20people%2C%20or%20an%20ideology.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01132828%2Fimage-1681.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01132828%2Fimage-1681.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01132828%2Fimage-1681-300x150.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01132828%2Fimage-1681-1024x511.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01132828%2Fimage-1681-800x400.png%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691177%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22599%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWhile%20much%20has%20been%20said%20and%20written%20about%20the%20mourning%20and%20memorialisation%20for%20the%20victims%2C%20the%20question%20arises%2C%20how%20does%20one%20memorialise%20perpetrators%3F%20Photo%3A%20Unsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-to-indict-persecutors%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20Indict%20Perpetrators%20%E2%80%93%20Nuremberg%E2%80%99s%20History%20Lessons%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20absence%20of%20%3Cem%3ECorpus%20delicti%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Videla%E2%80%99s%20time%2C%20there%20were%20very%20few%20%3Cem%3Ecorpus%20delicti%3C%2Fem%3E%20(evidence%20of%20a%20crime%20committed%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20corpse).%20Both%20the%20living%20and%20the%20dead%20were%20%E2%80%98disappeared%E2%80%99.%20As%20stated%20in%20the%20official%20report%20on%20the%20Argentinian%20disappearances%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.desaparecidos.org%2Fnuncamas%2Fweb%2Fenglish%2Flibrary%2Fnevagain%2Fnevagain_001.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENunca%20M%C3%A1s%3A%20The%20Report%20of%20the%20Argentine%20National%20Commission%20on%20the%20Disappeared%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(1986)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%5BThe%5D%20absence%20giving%20hope%20to%20the%20relatives%20that%20the%20kidnap%20victim%20would%20be%20freed%20and%20return%3B%20then%20the%20concealment%20and%20destruction%20of%20documen%C2%ADtation%2C%20which%20undoubtedly%20existed%20in%20every%20case%2C%20prolonging%20the%20uncertainty%20about%20what%20had%20happened%3B%20and%20finally%2C%20the%20nameless%20bodies%2C%20without%20identity%2C%20driving%20people%20distraught%20at%20the%20impos%C2%ADsibility%20of%20knowing%20the%20specific%20fate%20of%20their%20loved%20one.%20It%20was%20a%20bottomless%20pit%20of%20horror.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20thousands%20killed%20in%20the%20S-21%20prison%20of%20the%20Khmer%20Rouge%20during%20the%20years%20of%20terror%20were%20indexed%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwhy-atrocity-archives-exist-and-why-we-need-them%5C%22%3Ephotographic%20archive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20least.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20context%20where%20families%20and%20communities%20mourn%20the%20very%20absence%20of%20bodies%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20absence%20is%2C%20oddly%2C%20evidence%20that%20something%20is%20rotten%20in%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20the%20debate%20around%20the%20rights%20of%20dictators%E2%80%99%20families%20or%20the%20state%20itself%20to%20commemorate%2C%20memorialise%2C%20and%20thereby%20%E2%80%98honour%E2%80%99%20the%20dictator%20becomes%20a%20thorny%20issue.%20Take%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20case%20of%20Talaat%20Pasha%2C%20often%20seen%20as%20the%20man%20behind%20the%20Armenian%20massacres.%20After%20his%20assassination%20in%201921%2C%20he%20was%20given%20a%20grand%20burial%20in%20Berlin.%20Later%2C%20Adolf%20Hitler%20transferred%20the%20remains%20to%20Istanbul%2C%20and%20it%20is%20now%20in%20a%20mausoleum%20built%20in%20the%20memory%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98heroes%20of%20the%20fatherland%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Nazis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalww2museum.org%2Fwar%2Ftopics%2Fnuremberg-trials%5C%22%3Econvicted%20at%20Nuremberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20not%20subject%20to%20public%20executions%2C%20although%20the%20photographs%20of%20their%20dead%20bodies%20were%20released.%20Hitler%E2%80%99s%20body%2C%20at%20his%20own%20orders%2C%20was%20burnt%20immediately%20after%20his%20suicide%20in%20the%20Berlin%20bunker.%20The%20subject%20of%20where%20Spain%E2%80%99s%20Franco%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-46048514%5C%22%3Eshould%20be%20interred%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20tomb%20in%20the%20Valle%20de%20los%20Cai%CC%81dos%20or%20in%20the%20cemetery%20near%20his%20former%20residence%20in%20the%20palace%20of%20El%20Pardo%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20controversy.%20The%20same%20applies%20to%20the%20body%20of%20Pol%20Pot%20and%20the%20other%20leaders%20of%20the%20Cambodia%2FKhmer%20Rouge%20reign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20many%20massacred%20or%20disappeared%20do%20not%20have%20a%20topography%20of%20remains%20%E2%80%93%20the%20body%2C%20a%20grave%2C%20a%20tombstone%2C%20an%20annual%20prayer%2Fritual%20%E2%80%93%20how%20does%20the%20national%20or%20community%20mourning%20of%20the%20principal%20human%20cause(s)%20of%20the%20massacre%20operate%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20survivors%2C%20the%20tyrants%20by%20dying%2C%20escaped%20the%20processes%20of%20justice%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20law.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2006%2F8%2F10%2Fcambodias-long-wait-for-justice%5C%22%3EPol%20Pot%E2%80%99s%20trial%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20underway%20when%20he%20died%20and%20for%20many%20families%20of%20his%20victims%2C%20he%20had%20%E2%80%98got%20away%E2%80%99%20by%20dying.%20That%20is%2C%20the%20impunity%20with%20which%20they%20operated%20in%20massacring%20and%20maiming%20thousands%20when%20alive%2C%20extended%20to%20them%20even%20after%20their%20reign%20and%20to%20their%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShould%20the%20corpses%20of%20the%20perpetrator%20be%20treated%20as%20%3Cem%3Ecorpus%20delicti%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%20Does%20this%20corpse%2C%20of%20the%20perpetrator%2C%20bring%20about%20closure%20for%20survivors%20of%20those%20s%2Fhe%20had%20executed%3F%20Or%20does%20the%20very%20presence%20of%20the%20perpetrator%E2%80%99s%20corpse%2C%20often%20interred%20grandly%2C%20mark%20the%20transformation%20of%20the%20villain%20into%20a%20hero%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01140941%2FBundesarchiv_Bild_183-V04744_Berlin_Garten_der_zerst%25C3%25B6rte_Reichskanzlei-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221019%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01140941%2FBundesarchiv_Bild_183-V04744_Berlin_Garten_der_zerst%25C3%25B6rte_Reichskanzlei-1.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01140941%2FBundesarchiv_Bild_183-V04744_Berlin_Garten_der_zerst%25C3%25B6rte_Reichskanzlei-1-300x189.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691186%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22642%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EExterior%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Cspan%20title%3D%5C%22German-language%20text%5C%22%3EF%C3%BChrerbunker%3C%2Fspan%3E%20shortly%20before%20its%20destruction.%20Hitler%20and%20Braun%E2%80%99s%20remains%20were%20burnt%20in%20a%20shell%20crater%20outside%20the%20emergency%20exit%20at%20the%20left.%20Photo%3A%20Bundesarchiv%2C%20Bild%20183-V04744%2FCC-BY-SA%203.0%2FWikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrying%20memories%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judicial%20process%20operates%20as%20not%20just%20an%20occasion%20for%20remembering%20the%20horrors%20%E2%80%93%20many%20victims%20break%20down%2C%20as%20occurred%20in%20the%20Cambodia%2FKhmer%20Rouge%20trials%20and%20even%20at%20the%20South%20African%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20hearings%20%E2%80%93%20but%20also%20as%20a%20means%20of%20bringing%20the%20perpetrators%20to%20public%20account.%20This%20involves%20questions%2C%20practices%2C%20and%20the%20ethics%20of%20memory-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20perp%20is%20put%20on%20trial%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Nuremberg%201945%20to%20Cambodia%202009%20%E2%80%93%20what%20is%20being%20made%20public%20is%20a%20memorialisation%20of%20their%20victims%2C%20but%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20perpetrator.%20The%20testimony%20of%20witnesses%20%E2%80%93%20though%20this%20was%20not%20the%20procedure%20at%20Nuremberg%2C%20which%20relied%20on%20documentary%20evidence%20%E2%80%93%20against%20the%20perpetrator%20in%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20physical%20presence%20marked%20the%20verbal%20%3Cem%3Ecorpus%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Edelicti%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20and%20from%20the%20times%20of%20horror.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20trial%20is%20also%20a%20spectacle%20where%20the%20survivors%E2%80%99%20memories%20go%20up%20against%20those%20of%20the%20perps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20testimony%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fcambodia-horror-20-years-after-pol-pots-death%5C%22%3EVann%20Nath%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20survived%20S-21%2C%20gave%20the%20lie%20to%20the%20denials%20and%20evasions%20of%20Kaing%20Guek%20Eav%2C%20aka%20%E2%80%98Duch%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20commandant%20of%20S-21%2C%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eccc.gov.kh%2Fen%2Fnode%2F39457%5C%22%3EKhmer%20Rouge%20trials%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20defence%20stated%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDuch%20was%20just%20a%20minor%20Secretary%20who%20had%20no%20real%20authority%20to%20make%20decisions%20or%20to%20do%20anything%20contradictory%20to%20the%20directions%20from%20or%20the%20orders%20from%20the%20upper%20echelon.%20Therefore%20he%20could%20not%20be%20considered%20the%20most%20responsible%20person.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20own%20apology%2C%20Duch%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20the%20director%20of%20S-21%2C%20I%20did%20not%20dare%20to%20seek%20any%20alternatives%20to%20obeying%20the%20orders%20from%20the%20upper%20echelon%2C%20despite%20knowing%20that%20carrying%20them%20out%20would%20lead%20to%20the%20loss%20of%20thousands%20of%20lives.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20claimed%20that%20he%20was%20not%20present%20at%20the%20tortures%2C%20and%20did%20not%20even%20hear%20the%20screams%20of%20the%20tortured.%20But%20survivors%20like%20Nath%20testified%20to%20his%20presence%2C%20and%20thereby%20pointed%20to%20the%20manipulation%20of%20chronology%2C%20cause%2C%20and%20memory%20by%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20what%20is%20also%20on%20trial%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20victims%E2%80%99%20testimony%20is%20the%20public%20secret%20of%20murders%2C%20kidnappings%2C%20and%20disappearances.%20Cross-examinations%2C%20as%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Cambodia%20trials%2C%20bring%20together%20private%20victim%20testimony%2C%20perpetrator%20testimony%2C%20and%20historical%20records.%20The%20trial%20gives%20the%20public%20secret%2C%20available%20to%20many%20as%20personal%20or%20even%20shared%20memories%2C%20a%20visible%20form%20with%20images%2C%20documentation%2C%20interviews%2C%20etc.%20This%20transforms%20the%20public%20secret%20into%20public%20archivisation%20%E2%80%93%20a%20process%20in%20which%20the%20perp%20is%20%3Cem%3Epresent%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20although%20s%2Fhe%20may%20have%20been%20behind%20the%20scenes%2C%20%E2%80%98merely%E2%80%99%20ordering%20the%20heinous%20acts%20when%20they%20were%20undertaken.%20The%20public%20archivisation%20project%20is%20often%20framed%20within%20the%20principles%20of%20law%2C%20memory%2C%20and%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20aspects%20to%20this%20public%20archivisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20common%20sense%20tells%20us%20that%20perps%20on%20trial%20minimise%20their%20role%20in%20the%20genocides%20and%20massacres%2C%20and%20claim%20to%20be%20either%20simply%20following%20orders.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20can%20we%20call%20what%20the%20perpetrator%20states%20in%20court%20%E2%80%98testimony%E2%80%99%20or%20is%20s%2Fhe%20manipulating%20the%20memories%20to%20provide%20a%20different%20genealogy%20of%20the%20events%20%E2%80%93%20one%20in%20which%20s%2Fhe%20had%20little%20or%20no%20role%3F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.openedition.org%2Ftemoigner%2F5249%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%3EAnneleen%20Spiessens%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20argued%20that%20%E2%80%98the%20very%20possibility%20of%20the%20killer%E2%80%99s%20testimony%20is%20disquieting.%20How%20can%20a%20person%20be%20capable%20of%20telling%20this%20kind%20of%20story%20and%20voicing%20the%20ultimate%20transgression%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20when%20the%20perpetrators%20die%20before%20such%20a%20public%20archivisation%20process%20where%2C%20very%20often%2C%20they%20are%20called%20upon%20to%20confess%2C%20many%20like%20Videla%20carry%20their%20dark%20secrets%20to%20the%20grave%20and%20thus%20resist%20publicisation.%20For%20critics%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F13642987.2015.1032263%5C%22%3EMichelle%20Caswell%20and%20Anne%20Gilliland%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20deaths%20of%20the%20perpetrators%20means%20they%20escape%20this%20process%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20accused%20become%20forever-from-now-on%20unavailable%20and%20thus%20unassailable%20evidence%20%E2%80%93%20in%20essence%3B%20they%20are%20transformed%20into%20imagined%20documents%20that%20can%20never%20be%20cross-examined.%20In%20this%20construction%2C%20the%20would-be%20testimony%20of%20perpetrators%20is%20given%20epistemological%20validity%20over%20that%20of%20victims%2C%20offering%20up%20the%20false%20and%20unfulfillable%20promise%20of%20establishing%20a%20singular%20truth.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20victim%20testifies%20while%20the%20perpetrator%20confesses%2C%20writes%20perpetrator-and-film-studies%20theorist%20Raya%20Morag.%20But%20what%20happens%20where%20there%20is%20%3Cem%3Eno%3C%2Fem%3E%20confession%2C%20she%20argues.%20Caswell%20and%20Gilliland%20note%20that%20with%20their%20deaths%2C%20no%20cross-examination%20of%20the%20perp%20is%20possible%2C%20and%20one%20can%20only%20speculate%20on%20their%20intentions%20and%20psychological%20make-up.%20We%20imagine%20them%20as%20documents%20that%20provide%20a%20certain%20historical%20memory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20perhaps%2C%20there%20is%20a%20third%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20the%20public%20archivisation%20and%20memorialisation%20of%20perpetrator%20testimonies.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjpr.winchesteruniversitypress.org%2Farticles%2F10.21039%2Fjpr.v1i1.38%5C%22%3ESibylle%20Schmidt%3C%2Fa%3E%20argues%20that%20the%20perps%20are%20%3Cem%3Eauctor%20delicti%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20author%20or%20originator%20of%20an%20act%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20of%20murders%20and%20killings.%20Schmidt%20writes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20person%20is%20the%20author%20of%20a%20violent%20transformation%20of%20the%20state%20of%20the%20world%2C%20be%20it%20through%20his%20or%20her%20actions%20or%20omissions.%20The%20deed%20carries%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20his%20or%20her%20fingerprint.%20Perpetration%20has%20to%20do%20with%20authorship%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20structural%20political%20violence%20seeks%20to%20deny%20and%20conceal%20individual%20responsibility.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20brings%20together%20both%20testimonial%20narrative%20and%20memorialisation%20as-public%20archivisation%20here.%20Some%2C%20like%20Eichmann%2C%20Pol%20Pot%2C%20or%20Himmler%20may%20have%20been%20desk-murderers%2C%20issuing%20kill%20orders.%20Others%20like%20Duch%20were%20physically%20instrumental%20in%20carrying%20out%20the%20heinous%20acts%20%E2%80%93%20which%20the%20survivors%20recall%20at%20the%20trial.%20But%20both%20categories%20of%20perps%20are%20%3Cem%3Eauctor%20delicti%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20they%20authored%20the%20acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%C2%A0%20aspect%20is%20precisely%20why%20the%20bringing-to-trial%20%E2%80%93%20although%20it%20may%20not%20result%20in%20justice%20%E2%80%93%20is%20important.%20The%20trial%2C%20a%20public%20spectacle%2C%20is%20an%20act%20of%20public%20archivisation%20of%20the%20worst%20memories%20of%20a%20community%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20state.%20It%20points%20to%20the%20authorship%20of%20such%20acts%20that%20produced%20the%20various%20%3Cem%3Ecorpus%20delicti%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20even%20when%20the%20corpus%20is%20conspicuous%20by%20its%20%3Cem%3Eabsence%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20public%20archivization%20of%20both%20%3Cem%3Ecorpus%20delicti%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20more%20troubling%20%3Cem%3Eauctor%20delicti%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20crucial%20not%20just%20for%20the%20past%20but%20also%20for%20the%20future%2C%20as%20illustrated%20by%20all%20such%20genocide%20trials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20bring%20in%20and%20retain%20perp%20memories%20in%20the%20public%20eye%20is%20not%20about%20honouring%20them%20but%20to%20point%20to%20questions%20of%20authorship%2C%20of%20genealogy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98never%20again%E2%80%99%20slogan%20can%20only%20make%20sense%20when%20aligned%20with%20%E2%80%98never%20forget%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fpramod-k-nayar%5C%22%3EPramod%20K.%20Nayar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0teaches%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704105033000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01162813%2FIMG_2641.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhat-about-the-memory-of-perpetrators%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Should%20the%20corpses%20of%20the%20perpetrator%20be%20treated%20as%20corpus%20delicti%3F%20Does%20this%20corpse%2C%20of%20the%20perpetrator%2C%20bring%20about%20closure%20for%20survivors%20of%20those%20s%2Fhe%20had%20executed%3F%20Or%20does%20the%20very%20presence%20of%20the%20perpetrator%E2%80%99s%20corpse%2C%20often%20interr