3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fjapan-issues-tsunami-warnings-after-a-series-of-very-strong-earthquakes-on-the-sea-of-japan-coast%2Famp_articleshow%2F106451033.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Gang%20Offered%20Rs%2013%20Lakh%20To%20Men%20For%20Impregnating%20Women%2C%208%20Arrested%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEight%20people%20have%20been%20arrested%20in%20Bihar%20for%20allegedly%20offering%20Rs%2013%20lakh%20to%20men%20for%20impregnating%20women%20who%20could%20not%20conceive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20ran%20the%20racket%20under%20the%20name%20of%20%26quot%3BAll%20India%20Pregnant%20Job%20Service%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20police%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20arrests%20have%20been%20made%20in%20Bihar's%20Nawada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20said%20the%20accused%20would%20contact%20men%20through%20WhatsApp%20and%20social%20media%20offering%20them%20an%20opportunity%20to%20earn%20lakhs%20in%20return%20for%20their%20%26quot%3Bservice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20interested%20men%20were%20asked%20to%20pay%20a%20registration%20fee%20of%20Rs%20799.%20Once%20they%20would%20register%2C%20the%20gang%20gave%20them%20some%20photographs%2C%20asking%20them%20to%20pick%20a%20woman%20of%20their%20choice%20whom%20they%20wished%20to%20impregnate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20then%20asked%20to%20deposit%20a%20security%20amount%20ranging%20between%20Rs%205%20to%2020%2C000%20depending%20on%20how%20%26quot%3Battractive%20the%20woman%20was.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20men%20were%20told%20that%20they%20will%20be%20given%20Rs%2013%20lakh%20if%20the%20woman%20gets%20pregnant.%20They%20were%20promised%20a%20consolation%20price%20of%20Rs%205%20lakh%20even%20if%20they%20failed%20to%20impregnate%20the%20woman%2C%26quot%3Bsaid%20Kalyan%20Anand%2C%20Superintendent%20of%20Police%2C%20Nawada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20arrests%20were%20made%20after%20a%20Special%20Investigation%20Team%20(SIT)%20of%20Bihar%20police%20conducted%20a%20raid%20in%20Nawada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20have%20recovered%20mobile%20phones%20and%20a%20printer%20from%20premises%2C%20officials%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20efforts%20are%20on%20to%20trace%20the%20remaining%20accused%20-%20including%20the%20mastermind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKalyan%20Anand%20said%20the%20men%20are%20part%20of%20a%20countrywide%20cyber%20syndicate.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704101580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-11%2Fpnmgprs_pregnant-woman-generic-650_625x300_10_November_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fjob-scam-busted-in-bihar-for-offering-rs-13-lakh-to-impregnate-women-4780202%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eight%20people%20have%20been%20arrested%20in%20Bihar%20for%20allegedly%20offering%20up%20to%20Rs%2013%20lakh%20to%20men%20for%20impregnating%20women%20who%20could%20not%20conceive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fjob-scam-busted-in-bihar-for-offering-rs-13-lakh-to-impregnate-women-4780202%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fjob-scam-busted-in-bihar-for-offering-rs-13-lakh-to-impregnate-women-4780202%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fjob-scam-busted-in-bihar-for-offering-rs-13-lakh-to-impregnate-women-4780202%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Telangana%20Must%20Announce%20a%20Humane%20Prison%20Reform%20Policy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F01171400%2Fjail-prison.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20video%20circulating%20among%20long-term%20prisoners%20out%20on%20bail%20features%20Revanth%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20interview%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DWnhfqfzN5-Y%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9COpen%20Heart%20with%20RK%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%202015.%20Revanth%20Reddy%20had%20then%20served%20time%20in%20a%20central%20prison%20as%20an%20undertrial%20prisoner%2C%20accused%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fandhra-pradesh%2F2015%2Fjun%2F01%2FCash-for-vote-Scam-TDP-MLA-Revanth-Reddy-Gives-Murky-Twist-to-MLC-Poll-749301.html%5C%22%3Ebribery%20to%20legislators%20for%20voting%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20interview%2C%20he%20speaks%20of%20significant%20challenges%20faced%20by%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInequality%20before%20law%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20had%20granted%20Revanth%20Reddy%20the%20status%20of%20a%20special%20prisoner%20in%20June%202015.%20The%20prison%20authorities%20appointed%20a%20life-sentenced%20prisoner%2C%20Nagaiah%2C%20a%20Dalit%2C%20as%20his%20cook%20and%20assistant.%20Oblivious%20to%20unequal%20class%20and%20caste%20status%20before%20the%20law%2C%20Revanth%20Reddy%20genuinely%20admires%20his%20common%20sense%20regarding%20the%20political%20developments%20in%20the%20state.%20In%20a%20land%20dispute%20with%20his%20uncle%2C%20Nagaiah%20accidentally%20caused%20the%20death%20of%20an%20infant.%20Consequently%2C%20he%20was%20serving%20a%20life%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20offenders%20like%20him%20offend%20on%20a%20sudden%20provocation.%20The%20number%20of%20organised%20offenders%20is%20still%20relatively%20small%20in%20prisons.%20Organized%20offenses%20obviously%20require%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20literacy%2C%20technological%20skill%2C%20and%20resourcefulness.%20Such%20resourcefulness%2C%20of%20course%2C%20helps%20them%20to%20escape%20from%20the%20penal%20system.%20Consequently%2C%20they%20constitute%20the%20smallest%20minority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHardening%20attitude%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20often%20demonstrate%20an%20indiscriminately%20tougher%20attitude%20towards%20the%20prisoners.%20This%20harshness%20has%20increased%20tremendously%20in%20Telangana%2C%20signalling%20the%20rise%20of%20a%20new%20power%20elite.%20The%20state%20has%20released%20life%20prisoners%20only%20twice%20in%20the%20last%20ten%20years.%20During%20the%20same%20period%2C%20they%20were%20released%20four%20times%20in%20the%20neighbouring%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubluu.com%2Fflip-book%2F346034%2F793801%2Fpage%2F1%5C%22%3E2016%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%202020%2C%20Telangana%20released%20those%20who%20completed%20seven%20years%20of%20actual%20sentence%20with%20three%20more%20years%20of%20remission%20for%20their%20good%20behaviour.%20Although%20the%20policy%20was%20announced%20after%20a%20long%20break%2C%20many%20were%20not%20released.%20The%20reasons%20are%20many.%20Firstly%2C%20while%20it%20laid%20down%20five%20criteria%20to%20qualify%20for%20release%2C%20it%20exempted%2019%20categories%20of%20prisoners%20as%20disqualified.%20The%20exempted%20criteria%20include%20prisoners%E2%80%99%20indiscipline.%20Those%20who%20committed%20offences%20against%20women%2C%20children%2C%20NDPS%20Act%20and%20public%20servants%20were%20some%20of%20the%20categories%20declared%20ineligible.%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20Nagaiah%20is%20still%20languishing%20in%20jail%20as%20his%20offence%20is%20arbitrarily%20interpreted%20as%20committed%20against%20a%20child.%20The%20state%20declared%20that%20such%20prisoners%20will%20be%20released%20after%20completing%2018%20to%2024%20years%20of%20incarceration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubluu.com%2Fflip-book%2F346034%2F793824%2Fpage%2F1%5C%22%3E2020%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20number%20of%20disqualifications%20for%20the%20release%20of%20prisoners%20had%20increased%20to%2028%20categories.%20It%20declared%20that%20those%20who%20committed%20offences%20against%20public%20servants%20and%20girls%20would%20be%20considered%20for%20release%20after%2020%20to%2024%20years.%20The%20state%20also%20announced%20that%20life%20convicts%20previously%20detained%20under%20preventive%20detention%20laws%20are%20not%20eligible%2C%20even%20after%20completing%2014%20years%20in%20prison.%20%C2%A0The%20impact%20of%20this%20policy%20will%20be%20felt%20deeper%20after%20a%20decade%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Ftelangana-assembly-polls-detention-law-8997756%2F%5C%22%3Epreventive%20detentions%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20accused%20in%20all%20sorts%20of%20offences%20are%20increasingly%20invoked%20these%20days.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20state%20detained%20393%20offenders%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Fnationalcrimerecordsbureau%2Fcustom%2Fpsiyearwise2022%2F1701613297PSI2022ason01122023.pdf%5C%22%3E2022%3C%2Fa%3E%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20life%20prisoners%20have%20become%20deeply%20anxious%20and%20depressed.%20Previously%2C%20those%20who%20committed%20offences%20under%20the%20SC%20and%20ST%20(POA)%20Act%20were%20also%20barred%20from%20early%20release%2C%20but%20that%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20condition.%20It%20is%20not%20argued%20that%20those%20who%20offend%20against%20the%20marginalised%20should%20be%20jailed%20indefinitely.%20This%20is%20just%20to%20point%20out%20the%20changing%20political%20choices.%20But%20the%20irrational%20criteria%20for%20the%20release%20of%20prisoners%20must%20be%20removed%20to%20create%20a%20democratic%20and%20transparent%20method%20of%20reviewing%20their%20sentences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20democratic%20process%20for%20releasing%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20reasons%20exist%20for%20subjecting%20the%20prisoners%20to%20such%20an%20autocratic%20process.%20The%20first%20reason%20is%20that%20the%20system%20lacks%20an%20imagination%20regarding%20what%20constitutes%20reformation%20among%20prisoners.%20Furthermore%2C%20it%20lacks%20a%20method%20for%20capturing%20the%20transformations%20that%20prisoners%20undergo.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20this%20lack%20of%20imagination%2C%20the%20sentence%20review%20board%2C%20which%20is%20responsible%20for%20reviewing%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20sentences%20every%20three%20months%20under%20the%20law%2C%20has%20not%20met%20for%20decades.%20Consequently%2C%20the%20state%20has%20been%20deciding%20releases%20solely%20based%20on%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20committed%20crime.%20This%20implies%20that%20the%20system%20disregards%20the%20significance%20of%20depriving%20offenders%20of%20decades%20of%20freedom.%20It%20completely%20overlooks%20the%20goal%20of%20transforming%20the%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrison%20offers%20perspective%20to%20everyone%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interview%2C%20Revanth%20Reddy%20said%20that%20a%20month%E2%80%99s%20imprisonment%20has%20put%20his%20life%20in%20perspective%20and%20set%20his%20life%E2%80%99s%20direction.%20This%20is%20true%20even%20for%20ordinary%20prisoners.%20Years%20of%20imprisonment%20provide%20a%20direction%20to%20their%20lives.%20They%20can%E2%80%99t%20help%20but%20wonder%20about%20the%20fate%20of%20their%20lives.%20Their%20indefinite%20prison%20terms%20definitely%20tell%20them%20early%20on%20why%20their%20lives%20have%20taken%20wrong%20turns.%20Many%20prisoners%20realise%20that%20they%20can%20remain%20sane%20only%20by%20engaging%20in%20nonstop%20work.%20Deeply%20melancholic%2C%20they%20experience%20a%20sea%20change%20in%20their%20attitudes.%20However%2C%20the%20system%20does%20not%20create%20opportunities%20to%20get%20back%20to%20normal%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20prisoners%20a%20source%20of%20cheap%20labour%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevanth%20Reddy%20further%20speaks%20about%20how%20the%20prisoners%20were%20paid%20just%20Rs.%2030%20per%20day%20as%20wages.%20While%20it%20has%20been%20increased%20to%20Rs%2070%20now%2C%20Karnataka%20pays%20prisoners%20Rs%20663%20per%20day%2C%20Delhi%20Rs%20308%2C%20AP%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Rs%20200%2C%20Puducherry%20Rs.%20180%2C%20Bihar%20Rs%20156%2C%20and%20Odisha%20Rs%20145.%20The%20value%20of%20goods%20produced%20per%20inmate%20in%20Telangana%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Fnationalcrimerecordsbureau%2Fcustom%2Fpsiyearwise2022%2F1701613297PSI2022ason01122023.pdf%5C%22%3ERs%2052%2C331%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20year%2C%20which%20is%20second%20highest%20after%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20The%20revenues%20of%20the%20state%20from%20the%20prisons%20have%20soared%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftsprisons.gov.in%2FEOI.pdf%5C%22%3ERs%20800%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20year%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20wage%20paid%20in%20Telangana%20is%20difficult%20to%20justify%20by%20any%20standards.%20It%20is%20impossible%20to%20support%20their%20families%20with%20the%20meagre%20earnings.%20They%20save%20only%20Rs%2040%2C000-80%2C000%20after%20a%20decade%20of%20sweating.%20They%20allege%20that%20the%20government%20tightened%20the%20criteria%20for%20their%20release%20as%20the%20revenues%20from%20their%20labor%20soared.%20Revanth%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20government%20needs%20to%20examine%20the%20ethical%20implications%20of%20treating%20prisoners%20as%20cheap%20labour.%20Why%20can%E2%80%99t%20the%20state%20pay%20them%20an%20amount%20equivalent%20to%20the%20value%20of%20their%20labour%3F%20Instead%20of%20considering%20them%20as%20a%20source%20of%20cheap%20labour%2C%20thoughtful%20consideration%20must%20be%20given%20to%20their%20rights%2C%20their%20potential%20for%20reintegration%20into%20society%2C%20and%20the%20overall%20goals%20of%20a%20fair%20and%20equitable%20criminal%20justice%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPreserving%20social%20status%20quo%20is%20reformation%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevanth%20Reddy%20casually%20points%20out%20another%20thing%3A%20the%20prison%20authorities%20identify%20the%20professional%20experiences%20of%20the%20offenders%20%E2%80%93%20gardening%2C%20cooking%2C%20and%20haircutting%20%E2%80%93%20outside%20and%20assign%20them%20such%20jobs.%20It%20is%20unnecessary%20here%20to%20remind%20readers%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20professions%20and%20castes.%20This%20has%20been%20happening%20in%20all%20the%20jails%20for%20the%20last%20two%20centuries.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Findia-prisons-caste-labour-segregation%5C%22%3Einvestigative%20report%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20how%20caste%20governs%20prisons%20in%20Rajasthan%20has%20led%20to%20amendments%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcaste-prison-rajasthan-high-court-prison-manual-suo-motu%5C%22%3Eprison%20manuals%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently.%20Revanth%20Reddy%20must%20examine%20whether%20this%20relationship%20between%20caste%20and%20nature%20of%20work%20has%20been%20influencing%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20attitude%20towards%20low%20wages%20for%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReview%20prison%20practices%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%201984%2C%20politicians%20involved%20in%20the%20political%20feuds%20of%20Rayalaseema%20and%20the%20Naxalites%20were%20imprisoned%20in%20sizeable%20numbers.%20The%20governments%20had%20a%20stake%20in%20releasing%20them%20within%20five%20years.%20Since%201994%2C%20they%20started%20releasing%20them%20after%20completion%20of%20seven%20years%20as%20prisoners.%20These%20generosities%20were%20by%20default%20extended%20to%20ordinary%20prisoners.%20The%20strong%20rights%20movements%20were%20also%20vocal%20on%20the%20rights%20of%20prisoners.%20Their%20gradual%20weakening%20has%20left%20the%20prisoners%20defenceless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImplications%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndefinite%20sentences%20for%20public%20protection%20in%20the%20US%20is%20considered%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Flaw%2F2020%2Fdec%2F03%2Findefinite-sentences-the-greatest-single-stain-on-justice-system%5C%22%3Esingle%20greatest%20stain%20on%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20government%20must%20understand%20the%20ethical%20implications%20of%20these%20%E2%80%98never-ending%20sentences%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20prisoners.%20They%20create%20uncertainties%20for%20prisoners%20and%20their%20families.%20The%20lack%20of%20a%20specific%20date%20leads%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20hope%2C%20making%20it%20challenging%20to%20plan%20for%20their%20future.%20Without%20hope%2C%20what%20would%20induce%20them%20to%20motivate%20them%20to%20improve%20themselves%3F%20Indefinite%20sentences%20are%20a%20form%20of%20cruel%20and%20inhumane%20treatment%20of%20prisoners.%20This%20does%20not%20offer%20opportunity%20for%20their%20reintegration.%20The%20uncertainty%20damages%20their%20sanity%20and%20well-being.%20Given%20the%20pervasive%20inequalities%2C%20indefinite%20sentences%20impact%20certain%20sections%20of%20society%20more%20than%20others.%20The%20Congress%20government%2C%20which%20claims%20to%20restore%20democracy%20and%20civil%20rights%2C%20should%20comprehensively%20review%20prison%20policies%20and%20practices%20and%20their%20impact%20on%20the%20lives%20of%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMurali%20Karnam%20teaches%20at%20NALSAR%20University%20of%20Law%2C%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704101414000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F01171400%2Fjail-prison.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftelangana-must-announce-a-humane-prison-reform-policy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Telangana%20Congress%20government%20should%20review%20prison%20practices%20for%20a%20fair%20and%20transparent%20system%20that%20promotes%20prisoners%E2%80%99%20reintegration.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftelangana-must-announce-a-humane-prison-reform-policy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nobel%20prize%20winner%20convicted%20in%20Bangladesh%20labour%20law%20case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704101294000%2C%22