2https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106449146.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Frussia-declares-tsunami-warning-in-far-eastern-cities-tass-cites-mayoralties%2Farticleshow%2F106449146.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Frussia-declares-tsunami-warning-in-far-eastern-cities-tass-cites-mayoralties%2Famp_articleshow%2F106449146.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Frussia-declares-tsunami-warning-in-far-eastern-cities-tass-cites-mayoralties%2Famp_articleshow%2F106449146.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22''Daylight%20Robbery''%3A%20Man%20Pays%20Rs%20500%20For%20Rajma%20Chawal%20And%20Coke%20At%20Airport%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAir%20travel%20is%20considered%20the%20most%20convenient%20form%20of%20transportation.%20It%20provides%20a%20level%20of%20comfort%20that%20other%20forms%20of%20transportation%20may%20not%20offer.%20While%20travelling%20by%20air%20has%20certainly%20become%20more%20accessible%20for%20the%20salaried%20class%2C%20overpriced%20airport%20food%20despite%20its%20average%20quality%20has%20irked%20many.%20Recently%2C%20a%20man%20took%20To%20X%20to%20voice%20his%20frustration%20over%20spending%20Rs.%20500%20for%20a%20serving%20of%20%E2%80%98rajma%20chawal'%20and%20a%20coke.%C2%A0He%20likened%20the%20exorbitant%20food%20pricing%20with%20''daylight%20robbery''.%20However%2C%20he%20didn't%20disclose%20the%20name%20of%20the%20airport.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''I've%20never%20understood%20why%20we%20get%20fleeced%20at%20the%20airports.%20I%20got%20his%20simple%20dish%20of%20Rajma%20Chawal%20with%20a%20Coke%20for%20500%2F-%20bucks.%20Isn't%20that%20daylight%20robbery%3F%20Just%20because%20someone's%20traveling%20by%20air%20doesn't%20mean%20they%20have%20to%20be%20looted%2C''%20Dr.%20Sanjay%20Arora%20wrote%20while%20sharing%20a%20picture%20of%20his%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESee%20the%20post%20here%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EI've%20never%20understood%20why%20we%20get%20fleeced%20at%20the%20airports.%20I%20got%20his%20simple%20dish%20of%20Rajma%20Chawal%20with%20a%20Coke%20for%20500%2F-%20bucks.%20Isn't%20that%20daylight%20robbery%3F%20Just%20because%20someone's%20traveling%20by%20air%20doesn't%20mean%20they%20have%20to%20be%20looted!%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fq6dZEnwubV%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fq6dZEnwubV%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Dr.%20Sanjay%20Arora%20PhD%20(%40chiefsanjay)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fchiefsanjay%2Fstatus%2F1741115539072962810%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2030%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EReacting%20to%20his%20post%2C%20a%20user%20explained%2C%20''I%20was%20part%20of%20an%20Airport%20retailing%20company.%20The%20developer%20wants%20a%20minimum%20guarantee%20or%2026%25%20of%20revenue%2C%20whichever%20is%20higher.%20So%20at%20Airports%20you%20pay%20margin%20for%20Mnf%2BDistributor%2BDealer%2BRetailer%2BAirport%20Developer%2BTax.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20shared%20a%20similar%20grievance%20and%20wrote%2C%20''Last%20week%20in%20Kolkata%20airport%2C%20I%20had%20to%20pay%20Rs.%20300%2F-%20for%20one%20small%20cup%20of%20tea.''%20A%20third%20stated%2C%20''So%20true.%20Writing%20this%20from%20Bhubaneswar%20Airport%20where%20I%20just%20paid%20Rs.180%20for%20a%20cup%20of%20tea%20and%20Rs.100%20for%20a%20samosa!''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20fourth%20added%2C%20''It%20costs%20a%20lot%20to%20setup%20airport%20And%20it%20costs%20a%20lot%20to%20rent%20a%20place%20in%20airport%20and%20it%20costs%20a%20lot%20to%20employ%20people%20at%20airport%20as%20it%20is%20very%20secure%20place%20%26amp%3B%20hence%20it%20costs%20a%20lot%20to%20serve%20you%20food%20there.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''Part%20of%20the%20reason%20is%20the%20security%20provided%20by%20CISF%20at%20airports%20which%20is%20very%20expensive.%20Airports%20have%20to%20pay%20CISF%20for%20their%20services.%20This%20is%20not%20the%20case%20with%20trains%20and%20buses%2C''%20another%20person%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20similar%20incident%2C%20an%20internet%20user%20recently%20took%20to%20Instagram%20and%20shared%20that%20he%20was%20surprised%20to%20see%20how%20expensive%20dosas%20are%20at%20Mumbai%20Airport.%20The%20user%20stated%20that%20the%20price%20of%20a%20Masala%20Dosa%20with%20buttermilk%20was%C2%A0%E2%82%B9%C2%A0600.%20Even%20though%20items%20are%20sold%20at%20an%20inflated%20price%20at%20the%20airport%2C%20this%20price%20of%20a%20simple%20food%20item%20shocked%20many%20on%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704099840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fs4qfg7po_rajma-chawal_625x300_01_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fnagpur-man-pays-rs-500-for-rajma-chawal-and-coke-at-airport-calls-it-daylight-robbery-4780154%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20man%20took%20To%20X%20to%20voice%20his%20frustration%20over%20spending%20Rs.%20500%20for%20a%20serving%20of%20rajma%20chawal%20and%20a%20coke.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fnagpur-man-pays-rs-500-for-rajma-chawal-and-coke-at-airport-calls-it-daylight-robbery-4780154%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fnagpur-man-pays-rs-500-for-rajma-chawal-and-coke-at-airport-calls-it-daylight-robbery-4780154%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fnagpur-man-pays-rs-500-for-rajma-chawal-and-coke-at-airport-calls-it-daylight-robbery-4780154%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Selection%20of%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20Wide%20Variety%20of%20Work%2C%20All%20Collected%20in%20a%20Single%20Volume%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F06111059%2Fdiscover.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ERabindranath%20Tagore%20was%20a%20many-sided%20genius%2C%20who%20dominated%20the%20cultural%20landscape%20of%20Bengal%20during%20the%20late%2019th%C2%A0and%20early%2020th%20centuries.%20His%20output%20was%20prolific%2C%20flowing%20through%20poetry%2C%20song%2C%20novels%2C%20short%20stories%2C%20plays%2C%20essays%20and%20paintings.%20A%20century%20later%2C%20his%20work%20still%20stirs%20the%20hearts%20and%20minds%20of%20Bengali-speaking%20people%20across%20the%20world.%20However%2C%20Rabindranath%20was%20much%20more%20than%20a%20Bengali%20poet.%20He%20belonged%20to%20India.%20His%20writings%20embody%20a%20deep%20knowledge%20of%20Indian%20history%2C%20civilisation%2C%20culture%2C%20philosophy%2C%20and%20traditions.%20As%20a%20public%20intellectual%2C%20he%20addressed%20major%20social%20and%20political%20issues%20of%20his%20time.%20As%20an%20educationist%2C%20he%20established%20rural%20schools%20and%20also%20the%20Visva%20Bharati%20University%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinternational%20centre%20of%20humanistic%20values%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETagore%20wrote%20mainly%20in%20Bengali%2C%20and%20his%20work%20spanned%20many%20genres%20and%20thousands%20of%20pages.%20Though%20translations%20exist%2C%20the%20wide%20range%20of%20his%20work%20has%20not%20been%20accessible%20in%20a%20compact%20form%20to%20non-Bengali%20readers.%20A%20new%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Best%20of%20Tagore%3C%2Fem%3E%20edited%20and%20introduced%20by%20Rudrangshu%20Mukherjee%2C%20presents%20a%20diverse%20selection%20of%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20in%20English%2C%20collected%20in%20an%20elegant%20volume%20of%20about%20800%20pages.%20The%20book%20contains%20selected%20short%20stories%2C%20a%20novel%2C%20plays%2C%20essays%2C%20poems%20written%20for%20children%2C%20songs%2C%20and%20poetry.%20A%20few%20of%20the%20pieces%20were%20originally%20written%20in%20English%20by%20Tagore%20or%20were%20translated%20by%20him.%20But%20the%20majority%20is%20translations%20by%20other%20authors%20that%20have%20been%20published%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20introduction%20by%20Rudrangshu%20Mukherjee%20provides%20a%20short%20biography%20of%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%20(1861%E2%80%931941).%20A%20well-researched%20table%20details%20the%20main%20personal%20events%20in%20each%20year%20of%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20life.%20It%20also%20lists%20the%20major%20literary%20publications%20by%20other%20authors%20and%20the%20major%20historical%20events%20that%20occurred%20in%20that%20year.%20This%20provides%20a%20valuable%20backdrop%20for%20understanding%20the%20man%20and%20the%20context%20of%20his%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20early%20twenties%2C%20Rabindranath%20travelled%20extensively%20in%20East%20Bengal%20(now%20Bangladesh)%2C%20managing%20his%20family%20estates.%20This%20exposure%20profoundly%20influenced%20his%20creativity%20and%20social%20conscience.%20Tagore%20was%20moved%20by%20the%20beauty%20of%20nature.%20He%20also%20observed%20the%20difficult%20lives%20of%20ordinary%20people.%20These%20themes%20found%20expression%20in%20many%20of%20his%20famous%20short%20stories%20and%20poems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%201905%2C%20Rabindranath%20became%20politically%20active.%20He%20opposed%20Curzon%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20communally%20divide%20Bengal.%20Tagore%20supported%20the%20%E2%80%98swadeshi%E2%80%99%20movement%20but%20rejected%20the%20use%20of%20coercion%20to%20enforce%20the%20boycott%20of%20foreign%20goods.%20Nationalism%20became%20a%20recurrent%20theme%20in%20his%20writing.%20By%201906%2C%20he%20advocated%20initiatives%20for%20improving%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20villagers.%20In%20his%20own%20family%20estates%2C%20he%20established%20free%20health%20centres%2C%20primary%20schools%2C%20adult%20education%20classes%20at%20night%2C%20and%20also%20a%20rural%20bank%20to%20fight%20moneylenders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20depth%20and%20variety%20of%20the%20writings%20included%20in%20this%20book%20provide%20a%20comprehensive%20exposure%20to%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20creative%20endeavours%20from%20different%20phases%20of%20his%20life.%20However%2C%20one%20may%20ask%3A%20Why%20read%20Tagore%20today%3F%C2%A0%20Is%20he%20relevant%20to%20our%20life%20and%20times%3F%20From%20this%20perspective%2C%20Rabindranath%E2%80%99s%20writings%20can%20be%20broadly%20classified%20as%20follows%3A%20(a)%20Those%20that%20do%20not%20belong%20to%20any%20era%3B%20(b)%20Those%20that%20reflect%20a%20particular%20historical%20period%20and%20society%3B%20and%20(c)%20Those%20that%20address%20grand%20themes%20like%20civilisation%2C%20nationalism%20and%20philosophy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20301px)%2085vw%2C%20301px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01134418%2F9158SqaopUL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01134418%2F9158SqaopUL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20610w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01134418%2F9158SqaopUL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-183x300.jpg%20183w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691182%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22493%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Best%20of%20Tagore%3Cbr%3EEdited%20by%20Rudrangshu%20Mukherjee%3Cbr%3EEveryman%E2%80%99s%20Library%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20songs%20and%20poems%20belong%20to%20the%20first%20category.%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20songs%20are%20of%20exquisite%20lyrical%20beauty%20and%20their%20themes%20(love%2C%20nature%E2%80%99s%20beauty%2C%20the%20changing%20seasons%2C%20prayer%2C%20sorrow%20and%20hope)%20transcend%20time%20and%20place.%20Tagore%20composed%20over%202200%20songs.%20He%20said%20that%20many%20of%20them%20arose%20in%20him%20spontaneously.%20The%20book%20contains%20the%20translations%20of%2030%20of%20his%20best-known%20songs.%20Of%20all%20his%20writings%2C%20however%2C%20the%20songs%20are%20the%20most%20difficult%20to%20translate.%20In%20the%20original%2C%20the%20words%20and%20music%20blend%20magically.%20Their%20beauty%20transports%20the%20listener%20to%20another%20plane%20of%20awareness.%20It%20is%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20convey%20the%20subtle%20nuances%20and%20emotive%20content%20of%20these%20songs%20in%20English.%20Hence%2C%20it%20may%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20provide%20web%20links%20to%20the%20original%20songs%20that%20are%20available%20online.%20Readers%20of%20the%20translated%20lyrics%20would%20appreciate%20them%20more%20fully%20by%20hearing%20them%20sung.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2046%20poems%20in%20the%20book.%20They%20are%20powerful%20and%20beautiful.%20Their%20themes%20vary.%20I%20will%20comment%20on%20a%20few%20to%20convey%20their%20flavour.%20%E2%80%98The%20Spring%20Wakes%20from%20Its%20Dream%E2%80%99%20is%20famous.%20It%20records%20the%20poet%E2%80%99s%20actual%20spiritual%20experience%20in%20his%20teens%2C%20which%20awakened%20the%20fountain%20of%20his%20creativity.%20%E2%80%98I%20Won%E2%80%99t%20Let%20You%20Go%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20poignant%20poem%20about%20a%20little%20daughter%E2%80%99s%20reluctance%20to%20let%20her%20father%20leave.%20The%20poet%20sees%20in%20the%20little%20girl%E2%80%99s%20cry%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20eternal%20contest%20between%20love%20and%20inevitable%20farewell%20that%20resonates%20through%20all%20creation.%20Some%20poems%20are%20patriotic.%20%E2%80%98Now%20Turn%20Me%20Back%E2%80%99%20highlights%20the%20poet%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20a%20time%20of%20political%20struggle.%20The%20poet%20must%20sacrifice%20for%20the%20cause.%20He%20%E2%80%9Cmust%20walk%20life%E2%80%99s%20thorny%20path%20silent%2C%20alone%2C%20patient%20through%20joy%20and%20grief.%E2%80%9D%20In%20the%20iconic%20poem%20%E2%80%98Where%20the%20Mind%20Is%20Without%20Fear%E2%80%99%2C%20Tagore%20articulates%20his%20vision%20for%20independent%20India%E2%80%94free%20and%20fearless%2C%20independent%20yet%20open%20to%20the%20world%2C%20grounded%20in%20truth%20and%20justice%2C%20and%20shunning%20petty%20divisions.%20In%20%E2%80%98Pilgrimage%20to%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20Tagore%20sees%20India%E2%80%99s%20grand%20civilisational%20role%20as%20a%20great%20unifier%20of%20humanity.%20On%20India%E2%80%99s%20sacred%20shore%2C%20the%20poet%20says%2C%20down%20the%20ages%20successive%20waves%20of%20different%20races%20have%20arrived.%20India%20has%20absorbed%20them%20all%20and%20unified%20them.%20Her%20inclusive%20mission%2C%20to%20forge%20a%20common%20humanity%2C%20still%20continues.%20%E2%80%98The%20Flying%20Geese%E2%80%99%20(Balaka)%20is%20profound.%20Beside%20the%20Jhelum%20River%2C%20in%20the%20hushed%20twilight%E2%80%94the%20immense%20silence%20is%20suddenly%20broken.%20A%20flock%20of%20geese%20streaks%20across%20the%20evening%20sky.%20The%20sound%20of%20their%20fluttering%20wings%20transports%20the%20poet%20spiritually.%20He%20perceives%20the%20universal%20longing%20in%20all%20creation%20to%20merge%20with%20the%20infinite.%20There%20are%20many%20more%20poems%20here%20to%20delight%20the%20reader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20second%20category%20are%20his%20short%20stories%2C%20plays%20and%20novels.%20This%20volume%20contains%20seventeen%20short%20stories.%20A%20few%2C%20like%20Kabuliwallah%2C%20The%20Post%20Master%2C%20and%20The%20Hungry%20Stones%20have%20inspired%20award-winning%20movies.%20These%20stories%20reflect%20the%20social%20conditions%20of%20Bengal%20in%20that%20period.%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20keen%20power%20of%20observation%2C%20his%20sympathy%20for%20ordinary%20folk%20coping%20with%20life%E2%80%99s%20difficulties%2C%20his%20depiction%20of%20the%20social%20relations%20between%20master%20and%20servant%2C%20of%20the%20rigidity%20of%20social%20customs%20paint%20a%20vivid%20picture%20of%20rural%20life%20in%20late%2019%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20century%20Bengal.%20In%20many%20of%20the%20stories%2C%20the%20central%20characters%20are%20girls%20and%20women%20who%20confront%20social%20obstacles.%C2%A0%20%E2%80%98The%20Ghat%E2%80%99s%20Story%E2%80%99%20is%20about%20a%20sweet%20young%20girl%2C%20Kusum.%20She%20is%20married%20off%20as%20a%20child%2C%20is%20widowed%20early%20and%20returns%20to%20her%20village.%20But%20after%20the%20disgrace%20of%20widowhood%2C%20as%20she%20grows%20to%20be%20a%20beautiful%20woman%2C%20there%20are%20no%20options%20for%20her%20to%20experience%20normal%20emotions.%20%E2%80%98The%20Post-Master%E2%80%99%20is%20about%20a%20young%2C%20orphaned%20girl.%20She%20works%20as%20a%20domestic%20servant%20for%20an%20urban%20young%20man%20who%20is%20appointed%20a%20postmaster%20in%20her%20village.%20He%20is%20lonely%20and%20a%20misfit%20in%20rural%20society.%20The%20two%20form%20a%20sweet%2C%20innocent%2C%20almost%20brother-sisterly%20friendship.%20He%20starts%20teaching%20her.%20She%20takes%20care%20of%20him%20when%20he%20is%20ill.%20However%2C%20when%20he%20leaves%20the%20village%2C%20the%20power%20of%20the%20social%20barrier%20between%20them%20becomes%20apparent.%20The%20simple%20girl%E2%80%99s%20human%20feelings%20are%20real%2C%20but%20his%20attitude%20remains%20fundamentally%20transactional.%20%E2%80%98The%20Living%20and%20the%20Dead%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20strange%20tale%20about%20a%20young%20widow%2C%20who%20lives%20with%20her%20relatives.%20She%20loses%20consciousness%20and%20is%20mistakenly%20presumed%20dead.%20Her%20cremation%20is%20delayed%20inadvertently.%C2%A0%20She%20wakes%20up%20alone%20and%20escapes%20unnoticed%20from%20the%20unlit%20pyre.%20However%2C%20when%20she%20finally%20returns%20to%20her%20relatives%2C%20she%20finds%20it%20impossible%20to%20convince%20them%20that%20she%20is%20actually%20alive.%20The%20story%20reveals%20that%20identity%20and%20status%20are%20socially%20conferred.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98The%20Little%20Master%E2%80%99s%20Return%E2%80%99%2C%20portrays%20the%20feudal%20relationship.%20Raicharan%20is%20a%20devoted%20servant%20in%20a%20wealthy%20household.%20He%20has%20served%20the%20young%20son%20of%20the%20family%20since%20latter%E2%80%99s%20childhood.%20The%20young%20man%20eventually%20becomes%20the%20head%20of%20the%20family%2C%20marries%20and%20has%20a%20son.%20Raicharan%20is%20asked%20to%20look%20after%20the%20zamindar%E2%80%99s%20little%20son.%20He%20does%20so%20with%20love%20and%20zeal.%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20child%20drowns%20accidentally%20while%20in%20his%20care.%20Raicharan%20departs%20for%20his%20village.%20Soon%2C%20he%20has%20a%20son%20of%20his%20own%2C%20but%20loses%20his%20wife.%20He%20brings%20the%20child%20up%20like%20a%20%E2%80%98little%20master%E2%80%99.%20Having%20exhausted%20his%20resources%2C%20Raicharan%20finally%20takes%20the%20boy%20to%20the%20zamindar%E2%80%99s%20home%20and%20claims%20that%20he%20had%20abducted%20the%20zamindar%E2%80%99s%20child.%20His%20story%20is%20believed.%20The%20young%20boy%20is%20accepted%20by%20the%20zamindar%2C%20but%20Raicharan%20is%20kicked%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20stories%20cast%20a%20critical%20eye%20on%20the%20behaviour%20of%20the%20urban%20wealthy%20class.%20%E2%80%98The%20Patriot%E2%80%99%20exposes%20the%20hypocrisy%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98patriot%E2%80%99%20who%20boycotts%20Western%20cloth%20and%20wears%20khaddar%20but%20refuses%20to%20help%20a%20sweeper%20who%20is%20being%20thrashed%20for%20accidentally%20touching%20an%20upper%20caste%20individual.%20%E2%80%98The%20Laboratory%E2%80%99%2C%20published%20in%201940%2C%20is%20a%20critique%20of%20urban%2C%20wealthy%20Bengal%20society.%20The%20characters%20push%20against%20traditional%20boundaries%20and%20customs.%20Tagore%20is%20candid%20in%20his%20description%20of%20sexuality%2C%20seduction%2C%20inter-caste%2C%20inter-community%20and%20extra-marital%20relationships.%20The%20society%20is%20amoral%2C%20decadent%2C%20and%20commercially%20driven%2C%20in%20which%20the%20characters%20are%20cunning%2C%20manipulative%20and%20dishonest.%20Tagore%20criticises%20the%20contemporary%20Bengali%20male%20through%20the%20personalities%20of%20key%20characters%E2%80%93a%20scientist%20who%20is%20studious%20but%20unworldly%20and%20weak%2C%20an%20engineer%20who%20is%20brilliant%20but%20corrupt%2C%20and%20a%20professor%20who%20gets%20sexually%20manipulated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20third%20major%20category%20of%20work%20are%20his%20essays.%20In%20these%20works%2C%20the%20author%20addresses%20major%20issues%20of%20his%20time.%20During%20the%201920s%20and%201930s%2C%20he%20travelled%20extensively%20and%20lectured%20in%20Asia%2C%20America%20and%20Europe%2C%20where%20he%20spoke%20against%20blind%20nationalism%2C%20war%20and%20violence.%20He%20articulated%20his%20views%20in%20essays%20on%20nationalism%2C%20colonialism%2C%20and%20the%20crisis%20of%20civilisation%2C%20several%20of%20which%20are%20included%20in%20this%20volume.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20these%20essays%20were%20written%20a%20century%20ago%2C%20they%20remain%20surprisingly%20relevant.%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20message%20of%20universal%20humanism%20and%20cultural%20understanding%20is%20inspiring%20and%20thought%20provoking.%20A%20core%20argument%20running%20through%20them%20is%20that%20man%20is%20primarily%20a%20moral%20creature.%C2%A0%20Morality%20is%20grounded%20in%20affinity%20with%20nature%2C%20community%2C%20social%20bonds%20and%20cooperation.%20India%2C%20he%20says%2C%20should%20abandon%20the%20social%20customs%20of%20the%20caste%20system%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20generated%20a%20want%20of%20self-respect%E2%80%9D%20and%20also%20the%20%E2%80%9Clazy%20habit%20of%20relying%20upon%20the%20authority%20of%20traditions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20societies%20are%20mobilised%20into%20machines%20for%20material%20aggrandisement%20and%20organised%20aggression%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdense%2C%20poisonous%20atmosphere%20of%20world-wide%20suspicion%20and%20greed%20and%20panic%E2%80%9D%20is%20created.%20Colonized%20countries%20are%20exploited.%20But%20the%20rich%20also%20suffer%20by%20%E2%80%9Cbartering%20the%20higher%20aspirations%20of%20life%20for%20profit%20and%20power%E2%80%9D%20leading%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwreckage%20of%20your%20soul%E2%80%9D%E2%80%A6In%20these%20conditions%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20moral%20man%20remains%20behind%E2%80%9D.%20Our%20task%2C%20according%20to%20Tagore%2C%20is%20to%20reclaim%20our%20full%20humanity.%20For%20people%20of%20different%20races%20to%20thrive%20together%2C%20we%20must%20acknowledge%20real%20differences%20where%20they%20exist%2C%20and%20yet%20seek%20a%20basis%20for%20unity.%20For%20this%2C%20Tagore%20recommends%20the%20message%20of%20great%20saints%20like%20Nanak%2C%20Kabir%2C%20and%20Chaitanya.%20Human%20beings%20will%20have%20to%20exert%20all%20their%20moral%20power%20of%20love%20and%20clarity%20of%20vision%20to%20comprehend%2C%20what%20Tagore%20terms%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwhole%20world%20of%20men%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20much%20more%20in%20this%20volume%20and%20commend%20Rudrangshu%20Mukherjee%20for%20this%20excellent%20book.%20English%20readers%20will%20benefit%20from%20reading%20it%20and%20I%20recommend%20it%20wholeheartedly%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EChiranjib%20Sen%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20distinguished%20Pprofessor%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Studies%20at%20the%20BML%20Munjal%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704099632000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F06111059%2Fdiscover.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fa-selection-of-rabindranath-tagores-wide-variety-of-work-all-collected-in-a-single-volume%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Short%20stories%2C%20poems%20and%20essays%2C%20all%20translated%20in%20English%2C%20of%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20winning%20writer%2C%20offer%20a%20glimpse%20into%20his%20vast%20and%20varied%20output.%22%2C%22author%