20to%20be%20spot%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there's%20the%20second%20part%2C%20which%20is%20the%20welfare%20side.%20Most%20people%20haven't%20had%2C%20say%2C%20%C2%A35%20million%20in%20their%20life.%20So%20how%20would%20you%20know%20what%20to%20do%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20follow-up%20meeting%20with%20a%20legal%20expert%2C%20a%20lawyer%20or%20solicitor%20and%20a%20financial%20expert%2C%20there's%20a%20whole%20load%20of%20support%20for%20as%20long%20as%20they%20want%20it.%20We%20are%20very%20much%20not%20about%20just%20throwing%20the%20money%20at%20someone%20and%20running%20off%20into%20the%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20are%20a%20winner%20%5Bwith%20us%5D%2C%20you%20are%20always%20one.%20Some%20people%20keep%20in%20touch%20for%20us%20for%20years%20telling%20us%20what%20they've%20been%20up%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20that%20first%20phone%20call%2C%20it%20differs%20from%20person%20to%20person.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20just%20found%20out%20you've%20won%20%C2%A35%20million%2C%20you%20are%20probably%20going%20to%20be%20in%20shock.%20Your%20brain%20will%20be%20going%20a%20thousand%20miles%20an%20hour.%20You%20probably%20have%20lots%20of%20questions.%20Some%20people%20are%20literally%20gabbing%20away%20at%20me.%20Other%20people%20are%20very%2C%20very%20quiet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20some%20people%20take%20the%20day%20off%20work%20because%20they're%20waiting%20for%20my%20phone%20call.%20And%20I've%20had%20others%20who%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20at%20work%2C%20I'm%20actually%20going%20into%20a%20meeting%2C%20can%20you%20call%20me%20tomorrow%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20theory%20is%20everyone%20has%20their%20own%20version%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bjumping%20up%20and%20down%26quot%3B%20moment%2C%20whether%20that's%20whooping%20for%20joy%2C%20or%20sitting%20quietly%20on%20a%20beach%20by%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20people%20don't%20even%20tell%20their%20families%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20lots%20of%20funny%20incidents%20when%20people%20don't%20tell%20their%20loved%20ones%20about%20the%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20colleague%20of%20mine%20who%20went%20to%20see%20a%20winner%20who%20had%20a%20young%20baby%2C%20and%20the%20winner%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20my%20mum's%20coming%20over.%20Could%20you%20pretend%20to%20be%20the%20health%20visitor%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20there%20was%20knock%20on%20the%20door%2C%20my%20colleague%20had%20to%20hold%20the%20baby%2C%20as%20if%20to%20say%20she%20had%20a%20completely%20different%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20dealt%20with%20husbands%20who%20haven't%20told%20wives%20and%20wives%20who%20haven't%20told%20husbands.%20Some%20people%20don't%20tell%20the%20other%20half%20because%20they%20have%20some%20marital%20difficulty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20was%20one%20guy%20once%2C%20and%20I%20was%20at%20his%20dinner%20table%20completing%20all%20the%20paperwork%2C%20and%20he%20kept%20looking%20anxiously%20out%20the%20window%2C%20and%20asking%20me%3A%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20going%20to%20be%20very%20long%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20him%20I'd%20be%20another%20half%20hour.%20He%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BMy%20wife%20has%20gone%20to%20the%20supermarket%20and%20she's%20going%20to%20be%20back%20soon.%26quot%3B%20It%20turned%20out%20he%20hadn't%20told%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20think%20this%20is%20odd%2C%20but%20I%20love%20that%20woman.%20We've%20been%20together%2030%20years.%20I%20love%20the%20bones%20of%20her%2C%20but%20she%20doesn't%20know%20how%20much%20money%20I've%20got%20and%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20much%20money%20she's%20got.%20It's%20just%20the%20way%20we%20operate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20was%20something%20in%20his%20demeanor%20that%20made%20me%20think%20he's%20not%20lying%20to%20me%2C%20that%20it's%20just%20the%20way%20that%20they%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wouldn't%20go%20down%20very%20well%20in%20my%20house.%20But%20it%20was%20amazing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOccasionally%2C%20they're%20very%2C%20very%20suspicious%20of%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20handful%20of%20people%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20a%20real%20minority%20%E2%80%94%20who%20really%20struggle%20to%20believe%20it's%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20someone%20the%20other%20day%20who%20said%20to%20me%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20scamming%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sat%20there%20with%20this%20person%2C%20and%20he%20just%20didn't%20believe%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20me%20a%20while%20to%20persuade%20him%2C%20even%20though%20he'd%20played%20the%20lottery%20every%20week%20since%20it%20started%20in%201994.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%20every%20week%20for%20the%20last%2029%20years%2C%20you've%20been%20giving%20us%20money%2C%20and%20we've%20given%20you%20very%20little%20back%2C%20and%20you%20didn't%20think%20that%20was%20a%20scam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20now%20we%20are%20giving%20you%20some%20money%20back%2C%20and%20you%20%3Cem%3Edo%3C%2Fem%3E%20think%20it's%20a%20scam.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BGood%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20biggest%20surprise%20is%20how%20careful%20most%20winners%20are%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20that%20after%20the%202008%20financial%20crash%2C%20people%20became%20more%20financially%20conservative%2C%20and%20probably%20a%20bit%20more%20financially%20savvy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20misconception%20people%20have%20about%20a%20lottery%20winners%20is%20that%20everyone%20goes%20out%20and%20blows%20their%20money.%20It%20couldn't%20be%20further%20from%20the%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20public%20are%20overwhelmingly%20very%2C%20very%20conservative%20with%20their%20lottery%20win.%20The%20amount%20of%20people%20who%20go%20out%20and%20buy%20a%20Lamborghini%20is%20pretty%20low%2C%20percentage%20wise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20go%20and%20bu