20to%20the%20same%20species%2C%20say%20scientists.%20It%20could%20rewrite%20the%20history%20of%20our%20evolution.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Neanderthal%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e4e9fff0438955586558f24%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222342%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20employee%20of%20the%20Natural%20History%20Museum%20in%20London%20looks%20at%20model%20of%20a%20Neanderthal%20male.%3Cp%3EWill%20Oliver%2FPA%20Images%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUp%20until%20recently%2C%20the%20consensus%20was%20that%20Neanderthals%20and%20Homo%20sapiens%20were%20separate%20species.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20most%20humans%20carry%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.genome.gov%2F27539119%2F2010-release-complete-neanderthal-genome-sequenced%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBethesda%252C%2520Md.%252C%2520Thurs.%2Cin%2520Neanderthals%2520or%2520in%2520Neanderthals%2527%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2%25%20of%20Neanderthal%20DNA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20challenging%20the%20view%20that%20we%20are%20different.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOther%20studies%20suggest%20Neanderthals%20weren't%20inferior%20to%20Homo%20sapiens%20and%20should%20be%20considered%20human.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-riser-may-be-able-thank-your-neanderthal-dna-study-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeanderthals%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20long%20been%20portrayed%20as%20dim-witted%2C%20brutish%20monsters%20who%20were%20genetically%20inferior%20to%20our%20direct%20ancestors%2C%20early%20modern%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20ape-like%20creatures%20spoke%20in%20grunts%2C%20were%20beset%20with%20illnesses%2C%20and%20died%20out%2040%2C000%20years%20ago%20after%20losing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-humans-interbreed-with-mysterious-population-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevolutionary%20battle%20against%20Homo%20sapiens.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%20at%20least%2C%20that's%20what%20we've%20been%20told.%20Recent%20discoveries%2C%20however%2C%20are%20upending%20that%20view%20and%20reigniting%20a%20debate%20among%20scientists%20about%20whether%20Neanderthals%20should%20be%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20same%20species%20as%20early%20modern%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Neanderthals%20belonged%20to%20our%20species%2C%20it%20could%20reshape%20the%20history%20of%20human%20evolution%20and%20challenge%20how%20we%20define%20what%20makes%20us%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMost%20of%20us%20have%20some%20Neanderthal%20DNA%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20fossils%20of%20Neanderthals%20were%20identified%20almost%20200%20years%20ago.%20By%20now%2C%20you%20would%20think%20scientists%20would%20have%20made%20up%20their%20minds%20about%20whether%20they%20should%20be%20defined%20as%20a%20separate%20species%20from%20Homo%20sapiens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20turns%20out%20this%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20fierce%20debate%2C%20Antoine%20Balzeau%2C%20a%20paleontologist%20from%20the%20Museum%20National%20d'Histoire%20Naturelle%20in%20France%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20were%20at%20first%20discussing%20the%20fossils%20in%20the%2019th%20century%2C%20there%20was%20no%20real%20debate%20about%20specific%20species%20or%20not%2C%20simply%20because%20at%20the%20time%2C%20humans%20were%20seen%20as%20a%20species%20but%20by%20default%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20skull%20of%20a%20Neanderthal%20is%20seen%20in%20the%20foreground%2C%20the%20cast%20is%20partial%2C%20and%20missing%20bits%20of%20the%20skull%20are%20filled%20in.%20The%20skull%20is%20displayed%20in%20a%20museum%2C%20a%20person%20is%20seen%20in%20the%20background%20looking%20at%20the%20skulls.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657acc3850edbc52a86417bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221217%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20cast%20of%20a%20Neanderthal%20skull%20is%20displayed%20in%20the%20Chemnitz%20State%20Museum%20of%20Archaeology.%3Cp%3EHendrik%20Schmidt%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20fossils%20emerged%2C%20scientists%20started%20questioning%20the%20strict%20separation%20between%20the%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20up%20to%20recently%2C%20the%20consensus%20was%20mostly%20that%20Neanderthals%20should%20be%20seen%20as%20separate.%20The%20hominins%2C%20who%20roamed%20Europe%20as%20early%20as%20430%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20only%20briefly%20interacted%20with%20Homo%20sapiens%20emerging%20from%20Africa%2C%20who%20reached%20Europe%20about%2050%2C000%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lineages%20separated%20about%20500%2C000%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20relatively%20recently%20in%20the%20story%20of%20human%20evolution%2C%20but%20long%20enough%20ago%20that%20they%20looked%20significantly%20different.%20For%20many%2C%20that%20evidence%20was%20enough%20to%20close%20the%20debate%3A%20Neanderthals%20and%20Homo%20sapiens%20were%20separate%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20view%20started%20to%20change%20in%202008%20when%20Swedish%20geneticist%20Svante%20P%C3%A4%C3%A4bo%20achieved%20something%20that%20was%20thought%20to%20be%20impossible%3A%20he%20sequenced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-more-neanderthal-dna-others-scientists-why-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20genome%20of%20a%20Neanderthal%20by%20extracting%20DNA%20from%20ancient%20bones.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20his%20research%2C%20P%C3%A4%C3%A4bo%20was%20able%20to%20show%20that%20there's%20a%20little%20Neanderthal%20in%20most%20of%20us.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20showed%20most%20living%20humans%20carry%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.genome.gov%2F27539119%2F2010-release-complete-neanderthal-genome-sequenced%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBethesda%252C%2520Md.%252C%2520Thurs.%2Cin%2520Neanderthals%2520or%2520in%2520Neanderthals%2527%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2%25%20of%20Neanderthal%20DNA%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20also%20suggests%20that%20human%20ancestors%20and%20Neanderthals%20likely%20had%20children%20together%20when%20they%20cohabitated%20about%2050%2C000%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20news%20created%20a%20dogmatic%20rift%2C%20opening%20up%20the%20possibility%2C%20once%20again%2C%20that%20Neanderthals%20and%20humans%20should%20be%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20same%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20according%20to%20the%20strict%20biological%20definition%20of%20species%2C%20animals%20from%20different%20species%20shouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20produce%20fertile%20offspring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20definitely%20was%20a%20big%20game%20changer%20at%20that%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20Laura%20Buck%2C%20an%20evolutionary%20anthropologist%20studying%20hybridization%20between%20hominin%20species%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20has%20sort%20of%20brought%20that%20discussion%20to%20the%20forefront%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWere%20Neanderthals%20more%20than%20just%20our%20distant%20cousins%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20that%20species%20can't%20reproduce%20is%20%26quot%3Bintuitively%20attractive%20because%20it's%20sort%20of%20clear%20cut%2C%26quot%3B%20Buck%20said%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebut%20biology%20isn't%20clear%20cut.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20points%20to%20several%20examples%20of%20mammals%20that%20have%20been%20known%20to%20interbreed%20and%20have%20fertile%20offspring%2C%20like%20wolves%20and%20dogs%2C%20despite%20being%20clearly%20defined%20as%20separate%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20her%2C%20a%20better%20definition%20of%20Neanderthals%2C%20the%20most%20scientifically%20tried%20and%20tested%2C%20is%20the%20first%20one%3A%20the%20characteristics%20of%20their%20bones%20separate%20them%20from%20modern%20humans%20and%20their%20direct%20ancestors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222658%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Neanderthal%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5710f513dd0895b52d8b463b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222592%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHyperrealistic%20face%20of%20a%20Neanderthal%20male%20is%20displayed%20in%20a%20cave%20in%20the%20new%20Neanderthal%20Museum%20in%20the%20northern%20Croatian%20town%20of%20Krapina.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FNikola%20Solic%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20there%20are%20various%20different%20papers%20saying%20if%20you%20shaved%20a%20Neanderthal%2C%20put%20him%20in%20a%20suit%2C%20and%20put%20him%20on%20the%20tube%20or%20the%20subway%20in%20New%20York%2C%20no%20one%20would%20notice%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20that's%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we'd%20definitely%20think%20they%20looked%20a%20bit%20weird%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBalzeau%20agrees.%20%26quot%3BThere%20may%20be%20some%20discussion%20between%20specialists%20about%20how%20we%20define%20the%20different%20groups%20but%20from%20a%20paleontological%20point%20of%20view%2C%20Homo%20neanderthalensis%20and%20almost%20Homo%20sapiens%20are%20very%20clear%20anatomical%20differences%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Balzeau.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20others%2C%20however%2C%20the%20genomic%20information%20should%20be%20another%20argument%20to%20liberate%20the%20Neanderthal%20from%20its%20knuckle-dragging%20stereotype.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20case%20for%20Paul%20Pettitt%2C%20an%20archaeologist%20who%20specializes%20in%20the%20Paleolythic%20at%20Durham%20University%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20guesswork%20to%20use%20that%20evolutionary%20divergence%20to%20assume%20that%20there%20are%20different%20species%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECan%20culture%20define%20a%20species%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20digs%20started%20emerging%20showing%20Neanderthals%20may%20have%20been%20much%20more%20sophisticated%20than%20had%20been%20previously%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPettitt%20counts%20himself%20among%20those%20who%2C%20until%20recently%2C%20were%20skeptical%20that%20Neanderthals%20could%20have%20any%20sense%20of%20sophistication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUntil%20say%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20Neanderthal%20behavior%20was%20looked%20on%20as%20fairly%20stupid%2C%20or%20at%20least%20fairly%20limited%2C%20and%20Homo%20sapiens%20were%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20seen%20as%20quoting%20Shakespeare%2C%20as%20they%20dance%20across%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20joked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhich%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20nonsense%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20very%20entrenched%20view%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Neanderthal%20jewelry%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F550d4621eab8ea8153857882%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22507%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20is%20thought%20to%20have%20been%20Neanderthal%20jewelry%20created%20using%20eagle%20talons%20130%2C000%20years%20ago.%3Cp%3EAFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20relative%20to%20their%20size%2C%20some%20studies%20suggest%20Neanderthals%20had%20a%20brain%20at%20least%20the%20same%20size%2C%20if%20not%20bigger%2C%20than%20our%20ancestors%2C%20indicating%20that%20they%20may%20have%20been%20very%20cerebral%2C%20Pettitt%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20buy%20a%20top-of-the-range%20computer%20simply%20to%20use%20it%20as%20an%20alarm%20clock.%20There's%20got%20to%20be%20an%20evolutionary%20reason%20why%20Neanderthals%20had%20selected%20for%20this%20remarkably%2C%20metabolically%20expensive%20tissue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20suggested%20that%20Neanderthals%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneanderthals-hunted-cave-lions-feasted-meat-study-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewere%20skilled%20hunters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20hide%20workers%2C%20created%20rudimentary%20jewelry%2C%20had%20a%20complex%20lythic%20industry%2C%20and%20even%20worked%20with%20pigment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20scientists%20even%20believe%20they%20may%20have%20had%20some%20form%20of%20spiritualism%2C%20and%20would%20bury%20their%20dead%2C%20revere%20lions%2C%20and%20may%20have%20even%20created%20cave%20paintings%20%E2%80%94%20though%20that%20evidence%20is%20still%20a%20matter%20of%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Pettitt%2C%20this%20suggests%20that%20as%20Neanderthals%20and%20humans%20lived%20alongside%20each%20other%20in%20Europe%2C%20there's%20a%20good%20chance%20they%20shared%20a%20culture%20or%20learned%20from%20observing%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20spoke%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20can%20assume%20they%20probably%20spoke%20different%20languages.%20But%20that%20similarity%20suggests%20there%20was%20in%20fact%20a%20shared%20meaning%2C%20however%20simple.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECould%20Neanderthals%20be%20called%20human%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20bigger%20picture%20question%20at%20stake%20here%3A%20should%20Neanderthals%20be%20considered%20humans%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20humanity%20is%20very%20much%20depends%20on%20which%20group%20of%20people%20you're%20talking%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Buck%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20that%20is%20culturally%20defined%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20something%20that%20has%20sort%20of%20value%20judgments.%20We%20talk%20about%20inhumanity.%20We%20talked%20about%20humanity.%20It's%20not%20something%20that%20just%20refers%20to%20different%20types%20of%20organisms%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20sheer%20number%20of%20people%20who%20are%20alive%20today%2C%20there%20is%20arguably%20more%20Neanderthal%20DNA%20on%20Earth%20than%20there%20ever%20was%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAngela%20Saini%2C%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BSuperior%3A%20the%20Return%20of%20Race%20Science%2C%26quot%3B%20argues%20that%20there%20is%20a%20real%20risk%20of%20getting%20this%20wrong.%20Those%20who%20are%20thought%20to%20have%20more%20Neanderthal%20DNA%20today%20could%20be%20wrongly%20thought%20of%20as%20inferior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20studies%20have%20linked%20these%20Neanderthal%20genes%20to%20modern%20health%20effects%20like%20autoimmune%20diseases%2C%20diabetes%2C%20and%20some%20cancer%E2%80%94%20though%20how%20these%20genes%20exactly%20affect%20the%20health%20of%20the%20person%20who%20carries%20them%20is%20still%20mostly%20unclear.%20Neanderthal%20genes%20have%20also%20notably%20been%20associated%20with%20catching%20COVID-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20East%20Asian%20populations%20have%20been%20found%20to%20carry%20slightly%20more%20Neanderthal%20DNA%20on%20average%2C%20there%20is%20a%20real%20danger%20that%20this%20information%20will%20be%20used%20for%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20flip%20side%20is%20that%20our%20interpretation%20of%20Neanderthal%20culture%20has%20changed%20dramatically%20in%20recent%20years.%20Saini%20notes%20that%20the%20Neanderthal%20image%20was%20rehabilitated%20just%20as%20people%20started%20to%20draw%20them%20closer%20to%20populations%20in%20Europe%2C%20and%20genetic%20information%20started%20suggesting%20they%20were%20fairer%20skinned%20with%20red%20hair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20I%20find%20particularly%20galling.%20A%20hundred%20or%20so%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20supposed%20similarity%20between%20Neanderthals%20and%20Aboriginal%20Australians%20was%20used%20as%20a%20justification%20to%20draw%20living%20modern%20humans%20out%20of%20the%20circle%20of%20humanity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20WNYC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20because%20we%20see%20that%20Neanderthals%20have%20some%20relationship%20to%20modern-day%20Europeans%2C%20Neanderthals%20themselves%20an%20extinct%20species%20has%20been%20thrown%20into%20that%20circle%20of%20humanity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERewriting%20our%20history%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20still%20in%20the%20process%20of%20understanding%20Neanderthals%20and%20our%20relationship%20to%20them.%20As%20we%20begin%20to%20unpick%20the%20history%20of%20human%20and%20Neanderthal%20evolution%2C%20new%20scrutiny%20is%20being%20placed%20on%20the%20decision%20of%20scholars%20to%20separate%20the%20two%20and%20depict%20one%20as%20superior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20revealed%20his%20research%2C%20P%C3%A4%C3%A4bo%20reflected%20on%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-humans-interbreed-with-mysterious-population-2020-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBut%2520a%2520new%2520study%2520showed%2CInsider%2527s%2520homepage%2520for%2520more%2520stories.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehumans%3C%2Fa%3E%20living%20on%20the%20Earth%20today%20are%20rather%20exceptional%20%E2%80%94%20not%20necessarily%20because%20Homo%20sapiens%20are%20intrinsically%20better%2C%20but%20because%20there%20is%20very%20little%20time%20in%20the%20history%20of%20human%20evolution%20when%20Homo%20sapiens%20were%20the%20only%20hominin%20or%20human%20on%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHad%20Neanderthals%20and%20Denisovans%20survived%2C%20how%20would%20we%20deal%20with%20that%20today%3F%26quot%3B%20P%C3%A4%C3%A4bo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWould%20we%20experience%20even%20worse%20racism%20against%20them%20than%20what%20we%20experience%20among%20us%20today%20%E2%80%94%20because%20they%20were%20in%20some%20respects%20really%20different%20%E2%80%94%20or%20could%20we%20think%20differently%20and%20say%20if%20we%20had%20them%20here%20today%20we%20would%20not%20just%20have%20one%20type%20of%20humans%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20both%20things%20are%20possible%20and%20it%20sort%20of%20reflects%20our%20view%20of%20humans%20and%20how%20we%20speculate%20about%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%