20of%20the%20electorate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecularism%20and%20inclusivity%3A%20Beyond%20soft%20Hindutva%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20steadfast%20adherence%20to%20secularism%20and%20inclusivity%20significantly%20influenced%20their%20victory%20in%20the%20Telangana%20elections%2C%20distinguishing%20their%20approach%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-narrative-polls-bjp-hindutva%5C%22%3Esoft%20Hindutva%20stance%3C%2Fa%3E%20observed%20in%20states%20like%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20Karnataka%20was%20the%20only%20state%20that%20followed%20the%20Karnataka%20model%20in%20the%20November%202023%20elections.%20%C2%A0This%20strategy%20resonated%20with%20Telangana%E2%80%99s%20diverse%20populace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20to%20this%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Felections%2Ftelangana%2Felections-trelangana-cong-declaration-2765346%5C%22%3EMinority%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20bold%20initiative%20pledging%20substantial%20budget%20increases%20for%20minority%20welfare%2C%20up%20to%20Rs%204%2C000%20crore%20annually.%20This%20commitment%20aimed%20at%20uplifting%20minority%20communities%20through%20enhanced%20support%20and%20representation.%20The%20party%20also%20promised%20a%20caste%20census%20to%20ensure%20equitable%20distribution%20of%20resources%20and%20opportunities%20among%20all%20backward%20classes%2C%20including%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Odisha%20Congress%20Leaders%20Hopeful%20of%20Revival%2C%20but%20Is%20It%20Realistic%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fodish-congress-hope-revival-bjd-bjp%5C%22%3EOdisha%20Congress%20Leaders%20Hopeful%20of%20Revival%2C%20but%20Is%20It%20Realistic%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20Congress%20proposed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Ftelangana-polls-congress-releases-minority-declaration-promises-rs-4000-cr-budget-for-welfare%2Farticleshow%2F105110475.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eallocating%20Rs%201%2C000%20crore%20annually%20for%20subsidised%20loans%20to%20unemployed%20minority%20youth%20and%20women%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20augmenting%20their%20economic%20empowerment.%20The%20Abdul%20Kalam%20Taufa-e-Taleem%20Scheme%20was%20another%20significant%20measure%2C%20offering%20financial%20assistance%20up%20to%20Rs%205%20lakh%20to%20minority%20youths%20pursuing%20higher%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20also%20visibly%20embraced%20diversity.%20Leaders%20actively%20visited%20religious%20sites%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmunsifdaily.com%2Fa-day-before-polling-in-telangana-revanth-reddy-offers-prayers-at-temple-dargahvideo%2F%5C%22%3Evarious%20communities%2C%20including%20mosques%2C%20temples%2C%20and%20other%20holy%20places%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20promoting%20solidarity%20and%20respect%20across%20faiths.%20The%20inclusion%20of%20Dalit%20leaders%20in%20these%20visits%20symbolised%20a%20unified%20stance%20against%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comprehensive%20approach%2C%20combining%20welfare%20initiatives%20with%20visible%20inclusivity%20in%20religious%20engagements%2C%20broadened%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20appeal.%20It%20attracted%20not%20only%20minority%20communities%20but%20also%20voters%20favouring%20a%20secular%20and%20inclusive%20political%20framework%2C%20thereby%20fortifying%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20position%20and%20contributing%20to%20its%20electoral%20success%20in%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECivic%20synergy%3A%20NGO%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Es%20and%20the%20Congress%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelangana%20had%20its%20own%20version%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CEddelu%20Karnataka%E2%80%9D%20(Wake%20up%20Karnataka)%20movement.%20In%20Telangana%2C%20a%20consortium%20of%20local%20civil%20society%20organisations%20played%20a%20pivotal%2C%20albeit%20subtle%2C%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20political%20landscape.%20Groups%20such%20as%20Telangana%20People%E2%80%99s%20Joint%20Action%20Committee%20(JAC)%2C%20Jago%20Telangana%2C%20Bharat%20Bachao%2C%20Telangana%20Samakhya%20and%20Muslim%20Organisations%20JAC%20formed%20a%20robust%20network%2C%20echoing%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20various%20social%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20groups%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Felections%2Ftelangana-assembly%2Fcivil-society-organisations-back-the-move-for-change-in-telangana%2Farticle67570043.ece%5C%22%3EBharat%20Jodo%20Abhiyaan%2C%20led%20by%20national%20convener%20Yogendra%20Yadav%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20emphasised%20the%20need%20for%20a%20democratic%20India%2C%20where%20the%20Constitution%20and%20equality%20of%20all%20communities%20are%20upheld.%20Their%20stance%20was%20clear%3A%20to%20defeat%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20allies%20in%20the%20upcoming%20elections%2C%20both%20at%20the%20state%20and%20national%20levels.%20This%20movement%20saw%20the%20participation%20of%20hundreds%20of%20senior%20social%20activists%20and%20leaders%2C%20reflecting%20a%20widespread%20desire%20for%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20organisations%2C%20steered%20by%20influential%20civil%20society%20figures%2C%20became%20a%20collective%20voice%20for%20political%20change%2C%20working%20in%20tandem%20but%20not%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20Congress%20campaign.%20Their%20activities%20spanned%20organising%20events%2C%20mobilising%20public%20opinion%2C%20and%20active%20campaigning%20across%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20the%20Congress%20learn%20the%20lesson%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Telangana%20victory%20is%20the%20result%20of%20a%20well-executed%20strategy%20encompassing%20strong%20leadership%2C%20welfare-oriented%20policies%2C%20secularism%20and%20civil%20society%20support%2C%20all%20wi