%20brought%20in%20Tel%20Aviv%20District%20Court%20argues%20that%20defendant%20Roi%20Yifrah%20never%20served%20in%20the%20Israeli%20military%20but%20managed%20to%20make%20his%20way%20into%20the%20war%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prosecution%20said%20he%20did%20this%20by%20pretending%20to%20be%20a%20member%20of%20an%20elite%20combat%20unit%20belonging%20to%20Shin%20Bet%2C%20the%20domestic%20intelligence%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2035-year-old%C2%A0is%20also%20accused%20of%C2%A0stealing%20munitions%20and%2C%20according%20to%20Israeli%20media%2C%20of%20posing%20for%20a%20picture%20on%20the%20frontline%20with%20Prime%20Minister%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fbenjamin-netanyahu%2Ft-19234066%5C%22%3EBenjamin%20Netanyahu%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20media%20aired%20a%20photo%20of%20Yifrah%20in%20full%20battle%20gear%2C%20posing%20with%20other%20soldiers%20alongside%20Netanyahu%20at%20a%20helicopter%20landing%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20Israeli%20official%20insisted%20the%20prime%20minister%20was%20never%20at%20risk%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cseveral%20layers%20of%20security%20at%20the%20site.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYifrah%C2%A0faces%20several%20charges%2C%20including%20aggravated%20fraud%20and%20larceny%2C%20and%20could%20face%20up%20to%2036%20years%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsraeli%20far-right%20minister%20wants%20more%20Jewish%20settlers%2C%20fewer%20Arabs%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20far-right%20Finance%20Minister%20Bezalel%20Smotrich%20urged%20the%20return%20of%20Jewish%20settlers%20to%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20after%20the%20ongoing%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20radio%20interview%20on%20Sunday%2C%20Smotrich%20said%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20should%20be%20encouraged%20to%20emigrate%20outside%20of%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20have%20security%20we%20must%20control%20the%20territory%2C%E2%80%9D%20Smotrich%20told%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Army%20Radio%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20re-establishing%20settlements%20in%20Gaza.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20order%20to%20control%20the%20territory%20militarily%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20we%20need%20a%20civilian%20presence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmotrich%20is%20the%20head%20of%20the%20ultranationalist%20Religious%20Zionism%20Party%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20ruling%20coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20act%20in%20a%20strategically%20correct%20way%20and%20encourage%20emigration%2C%20if%20there%20are%20100%2C000%20or%20200%2C000%20Arabs%20in%20Gaza%20and%20not%20two%20million%2C%20the%20whole%20discourse%20of%20the%20day%20after%20%5Bthe%20war%5D%20will%20be%20completely%20different%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20help%20rehabilitate%20these%20refugees%20in%20other%20countries%20in%20a%20good%20and%20humane%20manner%20with%20the%20cooperation%20of%20the%20international%20community%20and%20Arab%20countries%20around%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20presence%20in%20Gaza%20began%20in%201967%20and%20lasted%20until%202005%2C%20when%20all%20troops%20and%20settlers%20were%20withdrawn.%20Hamas%20won%20the%20election%20in%20January%202006%2C%20and%20established%20full%20control%20over%20the%20strip%20after%20a%20clash%20with%20the%20more%20moderate%20Fatah%20faction%20in%202007.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20settlements%20on%20occupied%20Palestinian%20land%20are%20regarded%20as%20illegal%20under%20international%20law%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20they%20were%20approved%20by%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsrael%20appoints%20new%20foreign%20minister%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20government%20has%20approved%20the%20appointment%20of%20Israel%20Katz%20as%20a%20new%20foreign%20minister%2C%20to%20succeed%20Eli%20Cohen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%20will%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20replace%20Katz%20as%20Energy%20Minister.%20Cohen%2C%20however%2C%20will%20continue%20to%20serve%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20security%20Cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fbenjamin-netanyahu%2Ft-19234066%5C%22%3EBenjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0right-wing%20coalition%20government%20agreed%20last%20year%20to%20rotate%20the%20two%20positions.%20The%20appointments%20are%20subject%20to%20the%20Israeli%20parliament%E2%80%99s%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20the%20Cabinet%20also%20approved%20holding%20postponed%20municipal%20elections%20in%20February%2C%20also%20pending%20parliamentary%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20usually%20do%20not%20hold%20elections%20in%20wartime%20but%20these%20elections%20have%20been%20determined%20in%20advance%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20statement%20from%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20office%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20have%20already%20been%20postponed%20once.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael-hamas-war-netanyahu-says-war-to-last-for-months%2Flive-67860746%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20DW.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704081943000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25125403%2FNetanyahu.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisreal-palestine-updates-israel-appoints-new-foreign-minister%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20addition%2C%20Israel's%20far-right%20Finance%20Minister%20Bezalel%20Smotrich%20urged%20the%20return%20of%20Jewish%20settlers%20to%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20after%20the%20ongoing%20war.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisreal-palestine-updates-israel-appoints-new-foreign-minister%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Isro%20successfully%20launches%20satellite%2